#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/chapter05/gcc-pass1.xml:46
msgid ""
"GCC requires the GMP, MPFR and MPC packages. As these packages may not be "
"included in your host distribution, they will be built with GCC.  Unpack "
"each package into the GCC source directory and rename the resulting "
"directories so the GCC build procedures will automatically use them:"
msgstr ""
"GCC는 GMP, MPFR, MPC 패키지가 필요합니다. 이 패키지들은 호스트 배포판에 포함"
"되어 있지 않을 수 있으므로, GCC와 함께 빌드될 것입니다. 각 패키지의 압축을 "
"GCC 소스 디렉터리 안에 풀고, 생성된 디렉터리들의 이름을 변경하여 GCC 빌드 절"
"차에서 자동으로 이들을 사용할 수 있게 하십시오:"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><note><para>
#: en/chapter05/gcc-pass1.xml:52
msgid ""
"There are frequent misunderstandings about this chapter.  The procedures are "
"the same as every other chapter, as explained earlier (<xref "
"linkend='buildinstr'/>).  First, extract the gcc-&gcc-version; tarball from "
"the sources directory, and then change to the directory created.  Only then "
"should you proceed with the instructions below."
msgstr ""
"이 장에 대해 자주 오해하는 부분들이 있습니다. 절차는 앞서 설명한 대로(<xref "
"linkend='buildinstr'/>) 다른 모든 장과 똑같습니다. 먼저, 소스 디렉터리에서 "
"gcc-&gcc-version; 타르볼을 추출한 다음 생성된 디렉터리로 이동하십시오. 그러"
"고 나서야 아래의 지침을 진행해야 합니다."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><screen>
#: en/chapter05/gcc-pass1.xml:58 en/chapter06/gcc-pass2.xml:49
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<userinput remap=\"pre\">tar -xf ../mpfr-&mpfr-version;.tar.xz\n"
"mv -v mpfr-&mpfr-version; mpfr\n"
"tar -xf ../gmp-&gmp-version;.tar.xz\n"
"mv -v gmp-&gmp-version; gmp\n"
"tar -xf ../mpc-&mpc-version;.tar.gz\n"
"mv -v mpc-&mpc-version; mpc</userinput>"
msgstr ""
"<userinput remap=\"pre\">tar -xf ../mpfr-&mpfr-version;.tar.xz\n"
"mv -v mpfr-&mpfr-version; mpfr\n"
"tar -xf ../gmp-&gmp-version;.tar.xz\n"
"mv -v gmp-&gmp-version; gmp\n"
"tar -xf ../mpc-&mpc-version;.tar.gz\n"
"mv -v mpc-&mpc-version; mpc</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/chapter05/gcc-pass1.xml:65
msgid ""
"On x86_64 hosts, set the default directory name for 64-bit libraries to "
"<quote>lib</quote>:"
msgstr ""
"x86_64 호스트에서는 64비트 라이브러리를 위한 기본 디렉터리 이름을 "
"<quote>lib</quote>으로 설정:"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><screen>
#: en/chapter05/gcc-pass1.xml:68
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<userinput remap=\"pre\">case $(uname -m) in\n"
"  x86_64)\n"
"    sed -e '/m64=/s/lib64/lib/' \\\n"
"        -i.orig gcc/config/i386/t-linux64\n"
" ;;\n"
"esac</userinput>"
msgstr ""
"<userinput remap=\"pre\">case $(uname -m) in\n"
"  x86_64)\n"
"    sed -e '/m64=/s/lib64/lib/' \\\n"
"        -i.orig gcc/config/i386/t-linux64\n"
" ;;\n"
"esac</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><note><para>
#: en/chapter05/gcc-pass1.xml:77
msgid ""
"This example demonstrates the use of the <parameter>-i.orig</parameter> "
"switch.  It makes the <command>sed</command> copy the <filename>t-linux64</"
"filename> file to <filename>t-linux64.orig</filename>, and then edit the "
"original <filename>t-linux64</filename> file inplace.  So you may run "
"<command>diff -u gcc/config/i386/t-linux64{.orig,}</command> to visualize "
"the change done by the <command>sed</command> command afterwards.  We'll "
"simply use <parameter>-i</parameter> (which just edits the original file "
"inplace without copying it) for all other packages in the book, but you can "
"change it to <parameter>-i.orig</parameter> in any case you want to keep a "
"copy of the original file."
msgstr ""
"이 예는 <parameter>-i.orig</parameter> 스위치의 사용법을 보여줍니다. 이 스위"
"치는 <command>sed</command>가 <filename>t-linux64</filename> 파일을 "
"<filename>t-linux64.orig</filename>로 복사한 뒤, 원본 <filename>t-linux64</"
"filename> 파일을 그 자리에서(inplace) 수정하도록 만듭니다. 따라서 나중에 "
"<command>diff -u gcc/config/i386/t-linux64{.orig,}</command> 명령을 실행하여 "
"<command>sed</command> 명령이 수행한 변경 사항을 시각적으로 확인할 수 있습니"
"다. 우리는 이 책의 다른 모든 패키지에 대해 단순히 <parameter>-i</"
"parameter>(복사본을 만들지 않고 그 자리에서 원본 파일을 수정함)를 사용할 것이"
"지만, 원본 파일의 복사본을 보관하고 싶은 경우에는 언제든지 <parameter>-"
"i.orig</parameter>로 변경하여 사용할 수 있습니다."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/chapter05/gcc-pass1.xml:92 en/chapter08/gcc.xml:58
msgid ""
"The GCC documentation recommends building GCC in a dedicated build directory:"
msgstr "GCC 문서는 전용 빌드 디렉터리에서 GCC를 빌드할 것을 권장합니다:"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/chapter05/gcc-pass1.xml:98 en/chapter08/gcc.xml:63
msgid "Prepare GCC for compilation:"
msgstr "GCC 컴파일 준비하기:"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><screen>
#: en/chapter05/gcc-pass1.xml:100
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<userinput remap=\"configure\">../configure                  \\\n"
"    --target=$LFS_TGT         \\\n"
"    --prefix=$LFS/tools       \\\n"
"    --with-glibc-version=&glibc-version; \\\n"
"    --with-sysroot=$LFS       \\\n"
"    --with-newlib             \\\n"
"    --without-headers         \\\n"
"    --enable-default-pie      \\\n"
"    --enable-default-ssp      \\\n"
"    --disable-nls             \\\n"
"    --disable-shared          \\\n"
"    --disable-multilib        \\\n"
"    --disable-threads         \\\n"
"    --disable-libatomic       \\\n"
"    --disable-libgomp         \\\n"
"    --disable-libquadmath     \\\n"
"    --disable-libssp          \\\n"
"    --disable-libvtv          \\\n"
"    --disable-libstdcxx       \\\n"
"    --enable-languages=c,c++</userinput>"
msgstr ""
"<userinput remap=\"configure\">../configure                  \\\n"
"    --target=$LFS_TGT         \\\n"
"    --prefix=$LFS/tools       \\\n"
"    --with-glibc-version=&glibc-version; \\\n"
"    --with-sysroot=$LFS       \\\n"
"    --with-newlib             \\\n"
"    --without-headers         \\\n"
"    --enable-default-pie      \\\n"
"    --enable-default-ssp      \\\n"
"    --disable-nls             \\\n"
"    --disable-shared          \\\n"
"    --disable-multilib        \\\n"
"    --disable-threads         \\\n"
"    --disable-libatomic       \\\n"
"    --disable-libgomp         \\\n"
"    --disable-libquadmath     \\\n"
"    --disable-libssp          \\\n"
"    --disable-libvtv          \\\n"
"    --disable-libstdcxx       \\\n"
"    --enable-languages=c,c++</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/chapter05/gcc-pass1.xml:124
msgid "<parameter>--with-glibc-version=&glibc-version;</parameter>"
msgstr "<parameter>--with-glibc-version=&glibc-version;</parameter>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/chapter05/gcc-pass1.xml:126
msgid ""
"This option specifies the version of Glibc which will be used on the target. "
"It is not relevant to the libc of the host distro because everything "
"compiled by pass1 GCC will run in the chroot environment, which is isolated "
"from libc of the host distro."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/chapter05/gcc-pass1.xml:135
msgid "<parameter>--with-newlib</parameter>"
msgstr "<parameter>--with-newlib</parameter>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/chapter05/gcc-pass1.xml:137
msgid ""
"Since a working C library is not yet available, this ensures that the "
"inhibit_libc constant is defined when building libgcc. This prevents the "
"compiling of any code that requires libc support."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/chapter05/gcc-pass1.xml:144
msgid "<parameter>--without-headers</parameter>"
msgstr "<parameter>--without-headers</parameter>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/chapter05/gcc-pass1.xml:146
msgid ""
"When creating a complete cross-compiler, GCC requires standard headers "
"compatible with the target system. For our purposes these headers will not "
"be needed. This switch prevents GCC from looking for them."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/chapter05/gcc-pass1.xml:154
msgid "<parameter>--enable-default-pie and --enable-default-ssp</parameter>"
msgstr "<parameter>--enable-default-pie and --enable-default-ssp</parameter>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/chapter05/gcc-pass1.xml:157
msgid ""
"Those switches allow GCC to compile programs with some hardening security "
"features (more information on those in the <xref linkend=\"pie-ssp-info\"/> "
"in chapter 8) by default. They are not strictly needed at this stage, since "
"the compiler will only produce temporary executables. But it is cleaner to "
"have the temporary packages be as close as possible to the final ones."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/chapter05/gcc-pass1.xml:168 en/chapter07/gettext.xml:62
msgid "<parameter>--disable-shared</parameter>"
msgstr "<parameter>--disable-shared</parameter>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/chapter05/gcc-pass1.xml:170
msgid ""
"This switch forces GCC to link its internal libraries statically. We need "
"this because the shared libraries require Glibc, which is not yet installed "
"on the target system."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/chapter05/gcc-pass1.xml:177
msgid "<parameter>--disable-multilib</parameter>"
msgstr "<parameter>--disable-multilib</parameter>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/chapter05/gcc-pass1.xml:179
msgid ""
"On x86_64, LFS does not support a multilib configuration.  This switch is "
"harmless for x86."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/chapter05/gcc-pass1.xml:185
msgid ""
"<parameter>--disable-threads, --disable-libatomic, --disable-libgomp, --"
"disable-libquadmath, --disable-libssp, --disable-libvtv, --disable-"
"libstdcxx</parameter>"
msgstr ""
"<parameter>--disable-threads, --disable-libatomic, --disable-libgomp, --"
"disable-libquadmath, --disable-libssp, --disable-libvtv, --disable-"
"libstdcxx</parameter>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/chapter05/gcc-pass1.xml:190
msgid ""
"These switches disable support for threading, libatomic, libgomp, "
"libquadmath, libssp, libvtv, and the C++ standard library respectively. "
"These features may fail to compile when building a cross-compiler and are "
"not necessary for the task of cross-compiling the temporary libc."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/chapter05/gcc-pass1.xml:199
msgid "<parameter>--enable-languages=c,c++</parameter>"
msgstr "<parameter>--enable-languages=c,c++</parameter>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/chapter05/gcc-pass1.xml:201
msgid ""
"This option ensures that only the C and C++ compilers are built.  These are "
"the only languages needed now."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/chapter05/gcc-pass1.xml:208
msgid "Compile GCC by running:"
msgstr "GCC 컴파일하려면 다음을 실행:"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/chapter05/gcc-pass1.xml:216
msgid ""
"This build of GCC has installed a couple of internal system headers.  "
"Normally one of them, <filename>limits.h</filename>, would in turn include "
"the corresponding system <filename>limits.h</filename> header, in this case, "
"<filename>$LFS/usr/include/limits.h</filename>. However, at the time of this "
"build of GCC <filename>$LFS/usr/include/limits.h</filename> does not exist, "
"so the internal header that has just been installed is a partial, self-"
"contained file and does not include the extended features of the system "
"header. This is adequate for building Glibc, but the full internal header "
"will be needed later.  Create a full version of the internal header using a "
"command that is identical to what the GCC build system does in normal "
"circumstances:"
msgstr ""
"이번 GCC 빌드에서 몇 개의 내부 시스템 헤더가 설치되었습니다. 보통 그중 하나"
"인 <filename>limits.h</filename>는 시스템의 해당 <filename>limits.h</"
"filename> 헤더(이 경우 <filename>$LFS/usr/include/limits.h</filename> 를 차례"
"로 포함하게 됩니다. 하지만 이번 GCC 빌드 시점에는 <filename>$LFS/usr/include/"
"limits.h</filename>가 존재하지 않으므로, 방금 설치된 내부 헤더는 부분적이고 "
"독립적인 파일이며 시스템 헤더의 확장 기능을 포함하지 않습니다. 이는 Glibc를 "
"빌드하는 데는 충분하지만, 나중에 전체 내부 헤더가 필요하게 됩니다. 일반적인 "
"상황에서 GCC 빌드 시스템이 수행하는 것과 동일한 명령을 사용하여 전체 버전의 "
"내부 헤더를 생성:"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><note><para>
#: en/chapter05/gcc-pass1.xml:229
msgid ""
"The command below shows an example of nested command substitution using two "
"methods: backquotes and a <literal>$()</literal> construct.  It could be "
"rewritten using the same method for both substitutions, but is shown this "
"way to demonstrate how they can be mixed.  Generally the <literal>$()</"
"literal> method is preferred."
msgstr ""
"아래 명령은 백틱(backquotes)과 <literal>()</literal> 구축 형식을 사용한 중첩"
"된 명령 치환의 예시를보여줍니다.두 치환 모두에 동일한 방법을사용하도록다시작"
"성할수도있지만,여기서는이들이어떻게혼용될수있는지보여주기위해이방식으로표시했"
"습니다.일반적으로는<literal>()</literal> 방식을 더 선호합니다."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><screen>
#: en/chapter05/gcc-pass1.xml:236
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<userinput remap=\"install\">cd ..\n"
"cat gcc/limitx.h gcc/glimits.h gcc/limity.h > \\\n"
"  `dirname $($LFS_TGT-gcc -print-libgcc-file-name)`/include/limits.h</userinput>"
msgstr ""
"<userinput remap=\"install\">cd ..\n"
"cat gcc/limitx.h gcc/glimits.h gcc/limity.h > \\\n"
"  `dirname $($LFS_TGT-gcc -print-libgcc-file-name)`/include/limits.h</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/chapter05/gcc-pass1.xml:244 en/chapter05/libstdc++.xml:134
#: en/chapter06/gcc-pass2.xml:180
msgid ""
"Details on this package are located in <xref linkend=\"contents-gcc\" "
"role=\".\"/>"
msgstr "이 패키지 상세 정보 <xref linkend=\"contents-gcc\" role=\".\"/>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect1info><address>
#: en/chapter05/glibc.xml:14 en/chapter08/glibc.xml:14
#, no-wrap
msgid "&glibc-url;"
msgstr "&glibc-url;"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect1info>
#: en/chapter05/glibc.xml:12 en/chapter08/glibc.xml:12
msgid ""
"<productname>glibc</productname> <productnumber>&glibc-version;</"
"productnumber> <placeholder type=\"address\" id=\"0\"/>"
msgstr ""
"<productname>glibc</productname> <productnumber>&glibc-version;</"
"productnumber> <placeholder type=\"address\" id=\"0\"/>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><indexterm><secondary>
#: en/chapter05/glibc.xml:21 en/chapter06/bash.xml:21
#: en/chapter06/coreutils.xml:21 en/chapter06/diffutils.xml:21
#: en/chapter06/file.xml:21 en/chapter06/findutils.xml:21
#: en/chapter06/gawk.xml:21 en/chapter06/grep.xml:21 en/chapter06/gzip.xml:21
#: en/chapter06/m4.xml:21 en/chapter06/make.xml:20 en/chapter06/ncurses.xml:21
#: en/chapter06/patch.xml:21 en/chapter06/sed.xml:21 en/chapter06/tar.xml:21
#: en/chapter06/xz.xml:21 en/chapter07/bison.xml:21 en/chapter07/gettext.xml:21
#: en/chapter07/perl.xml:21 en/chapter07/util-linux.xml:21
msgid "tools"
msgstr "tools"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><segmentedlist><seglistitem><seg>
#: en/chapter05/glibc.xml:36
msgid "&glibc-tmp-sbu;"
msgstr "&glibc-tmp-sbu;"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><segmentedlist><seglistitem><seg>
#: en/chapter05/glibc.xml:37
msgid "&glibc-tmp-du;"
msgstr "&glibc-tmp-du;"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><title>
#: en/chapter05/glibc.xml:44 en/chapter08/glibc.xml:44
msgid "Installation of Glibc"
msgstr "Glibc 설치"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/chapter05/glibc.xml:46
msgid ""
"First, create a symbolic link for LSB compliance. Additionally, for x86_64, "
"create a compatibility symbolic link required for proper operation of the "
"dynamic library loader:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><screen>
#: en/chapter05/glibc.xml:50
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<userinput remap=\"pre\">case $(uname -m) in\n"
"    i?86)   ln -sfv ld-linux.so.2 $LFS/lib/ld-lsb.so.3\n"
"    ;;\n"
"    x86_64) ln -sfv ../lib/ld-linux-x86-64.so.2 $LFS/lib64\n"
"            ln -sfv ../lib/ld-linux-x86-64.so.2 $LFS/lib64/ld-lsb-x86-64.so.3\n"
"    ;;\n"
"esac</userinput>"
msgstr ""
"<userinput remap=\"pre\">case $(uname -m) in\n"
"    i?86)   ln -sfv ld-linux.so.2 $LFS/lib/ld-lsb.so.3\n"
"    ;;\n"
"    x86_64) ln -sfv ../lib/ld-linux-x86-64.so.2 $LFS/lib64\n"
"            ln -sfv ../lib/ld-linux-x86-64.so.2 $LFS/lib64/ld-lsb-x86-64.so.3\n"
"    ;;\n"
"esac</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><note><para>
#: en/chapter05/glibc.xml:60
msgid ""
"The above command is correct.  The <command>ln</command> command has several "
"syntactic versions, so be sure to check <command>info coreutils ln</command> "
"and <ulink role='man' url='&man;ln.1'>ln(1)</ulink> before reporting what "
"may appear to be an error."
msgstr ""
"위의 명령은 올바릅니다. <command>ln</command> 명령에는 여러 구문 버전이 있으"
"므로, 에러라고 생각되는 부분을 보고하기 전에 반드시 <command>info coreutils "
"ln</command> 및 <ulink role='man' url='&man;ln.1'>ln(1)</ulink> 확인하십시오."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/chapter05/glibc.xml:68
msgid ""
"Some of the Glibc programs use the non-FHS-compliant <filename "
"class=\"directory\">/var/db</filename> directory to store their runtime "
"data. Apply the following patch to make such programs store their runtime "
"data in the FHS-compliant locations:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><screen>
#: en/chapter05/glibc.xml:73 en/chapter08/glibc.xml:55
#, no-wrap
msgid "<userinput remap=\"pre\">patch -Np1 -i ../&glibc-fhs-patch;</userinput>"
msgstr "<userinput remap=\"pre\">patch -Np1 -i ../&glibc-fhs-patch;</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/chapter05/glibc.xml:75 en/chapter08/glibc.xml:65
msgid ""
"The Glibc documentation recommends building Glibc in a dedicated build "
"directory:"
msgstr "Glibc 문서는 별도의 전용 빌드 디렉터리에서 Glibc를 빌드할 것을 권장:"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/chapter05/glibc.xml:81
msgid ""
"Ensure that the <command>ldconfig</command> and <command>sln</command> "
"utilities are installed into <filename class=\"directory\">/usr/sbin</"
"filename>:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><screen>
#: en/chapter05/glibc.xml:85 en/chapter08/glibc.xml:75
#, no-wrap
msgid "<userinput remap=\"pre\">echo \"rootsbindir=/usr/sbin\" &gt; configparms</userinput>"
msgstr "<userinput remap=\"pre\">echo \"rootsbindir=/usr/sbin\" &gt; configparms</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/chapter05/glibc.xml:87
msgid "Next, prepare Glibc for compilation:"
msgstr "다음, 컴파일 용 glibc 준비:"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><screen>
#: en/chapter05/glibc.xml:89
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<userinput remap=\"configure\">../configure                             \\\n"
"      --prefix=/usr                      \\\n"
"      --host=$LFS_TGT                    \\\n"
"      --build=$(../scripts/config.guess) \\\n"
"      --disable-nscd                     \\\n"
"      libc_cv_slibdir=/usr/lib           \\\n"
"      --enable-kernel=&min-kernel;</userinput>"
msgstr ""
"<userinput remap=\"configure\">../configure                             \\\n"
"      --prefix=/usr                      \\\n"
"      --host=$LFS_TGT                    \\\n"
"      --build=$(../scripts/config.guess) \\\n"
"      --disable-nscd                     \\\n"
"      libc_cv_slibdir=/usr/lib           \\\n"
"      --enable-kernel=&min-kernel;</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/chapter05/glibc.xml:101
msgid ""
"<parameter>--host=$LFS_TGT, --build=$(../scripts/config.guess)</parameter>"
msgstr ""
"<parameter>--host=$LFS_TGT, --build=$(../scripts/config.guess)</parameter>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/chapter05/glibc.xml:103
msgid ""
"The combined effect of these switches is that Glibc's build system "
"configures itself to be cross-compiled, using the cross-linker and cross-"
"compiler in <filename class=\"directory\">$LFS/tools</filename>."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/chapter05/glibc.xml:110 en/chapter08/glibc.xml:98
msgid "<parameter>--enable-kernel=&min-kernel;</parameter>"
msgstr "<parameter>--enable-kernel=&min-kernel;</parameter>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/chapter05/glibc.xml:112
msgid ""
"This tells Glibc to compile the library with support for &min-kernel; and "
"later Linux kernels.  Workarounds for older kernels are not enabled."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/chapter05/glibc.xml:119 en/chapter08/glibc.xml:128
msgid "<parameter>libc_cv_slibdir=/usr/lib</parameter>"
msgstr "<parameter>libc_cv_slibdir=/usr/lib</parameter>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/chapter05/glibc.xml:121
msgid ""
"This ensures that the library is installed in /usr/lib instead of the "
"default /lib64 on 64-bit machines."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/chapter05/glibc.xml:127 en/chapter08/glibc.xml:120
msgid "<parameter>--disable-nscd</parameter>"
msgstr "<parameter>--disable-nscd</parameter>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/chapter05/glibc.xml:129 en/chapter08/glibc.xml:122
msgid "Do not build the name service cache daemon which is no longer used."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/chapter05/glibc.xml:136
msgid "During this stage the following warning might appear:"
msgstr "이 단계 중에 나타날 수 있는 경고:"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><blockquote><screen>
#: en/chapter05/glibc.xml:139
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<computeroutput>configure: WARNING:\n"
"*** These auxiliary programs are missing or\n"
"*** incompatible versions: msgfmt\n"
"*** some features will be disabled.\n"
"*** Check the INSTALL file for required versions.</computeroutput>"
msgstr ""
"<computeroutput>configure: WARNING:\n"
"*** These auxiliary programs are missing or\n"
"*** incompatible versions: msgfmt\n"
"*** some features will be disabled.\n"
"*** Check the INSTALL file for required versions.</computeroutput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/chapter05/glibc.xml:146
msgid ""
"The missing or incompatible <command>msgfmt</command> program is generally "
"harmless. This <command>msgfmt</command> program is part of the Gettext "
"package, which the host distribution should provide."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><note><para>
#: en/chapter05/glibc.xml:150
msgid ""
"There have been reports that this package may fail when building as a "
"<quote>parallel make.</quote> If that occurs, rerun the make command with "
"the <option>-j1</option> option."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/chapter05/glibc.xml:154 en/chapter06/bash.xml:69
#: en/chapter06/binutils-pass2.xml:101 en/chapter06/coreutils.xml:73
#: en/chapter06/diffutils.xml:80 en/chapter06/file.xml:81
#: en/chapter06/findutils.xml:53 en/chapter06/gawk.xml:56
#: en/chapter06/gcc-pass2.xml:158 en/chapter06/grep.xml:52
#: en/chapter06/gzip.xml:50 en/chapter06/m4.xml:57 en/chapter06/make.xml:51
#: en/chapter06/ncurses.xml:147 en/chapter06/patch.xml:52
#: en/chapter06/sed.xml:52 en/chapter06/tar.xml:52 en/chapter06/xz.xml:54
#: en/chapter07/bison.xml:64 en/chapter07/gettext.xml:71
#: en/chapter07/perl.xml:102 en/chapter07/python.xml:87
#: en/chapter07/texinfo.xml:50 en/chapter07/util-linux.xml:120
#: en/chapter08/acl.xml:51 en/chapter08/attr.xml:51
#: en/chapter08/autoconf.xml:48 en/chapter08/automake.xml:52
#: en/chapter08/bash.xml:65 en/chapter08/bc.xml:82 en/chapter08/binutils.xml:95
#: en/chapter08/bison.xml:47 en/chapter08/coreutils.xml:123
#: en/chapter08/dbus.xml:71 en/chapter08/diffutils.xml:48
#: en/chapter08/e2fsprogs.xml:88 en/chapter08/expat.xml:50
#: en/chapter08/file.xml:48 en/chapter08/findutils.xml:79
