msgid "Compile the package:"
msgstr "패키지 컴파일:"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><warning><para>
#: en/chapter05/glibc.xml:160
msgid ""
"If <envar>LFS</envar> is not properly set, and despite the recommendations, "
"you are building as <systemitem class=\"username\">root</systemitem>, the "
"next command will install the newly built Glibc to your host system, which "
"will almost certainly render it unusable. So double-check that the "
"environment is correctly set, and that you are not &root;, before running "
"the following command."
msgstr ""
"만약 <envar>LFS</envar> 제대로 설정되지 않았는데 권장 사항을 무시하고 "
"<systemitem class=\"username\">root</systemitem> 로 빌드 중이라면, 다음 명령"
"은 새로 빌드된 Glibc를 호스트 시스템에 설치할 것이며, 이는 거의 확실하게 시스"
"템을 못쓰게 만들 것입니다. 그러니 다음 명령을 실행하기 전에 환경이 올바르게 "
"설정되었는지, 그리고 &root; 아닌지 다시 한번 확인하십시오."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><screen>
#: en/chapter05/glibc.xml:167 en/chapter05/libstdc++.xml:122
#: en/chapter06/bash.xml:75 en/chapter06/binutils-pass2.xml:107
#: en/chapter06/coreutils.xml:79 en/chapter06/diffutils.xml:86
#: en/chapter06/file.xml:87 en/chapter06/findutils.xml:59
#: en/chapter06/gawk.xml:62 en/chapter06/gcc-pass2.xml:164
#: en/chapter06/grep.xml:58 en/chapter06/gzip.xml:56 en/chapter06/m4.xml:63
#: en/chapter06/make.xml:57 en/chapter06/patch.xml:58 en/chapter06/sed.xml:58
#: en/chapter06/tar.xml:58 en/chapter06/xz.xml:60
#, no-wrap
msgid "<userinput remap=\"install\">make DESTDIR=$LFS install</userinput>"
msgstr "<userinput remap=\"install\">make DESTDIR=$LFS install</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><variablelist><title>
#: en/chapter05/glibc.xml:170
msgid "The meaning of the <command>make install</command> option:"
msgstr "The meaning of the <command>make install</command> option:"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/chapter05/glibc.xml:173
msgid "<parameter>DESTDIR=$LFS</parameter>"
msgstr "<parameter>DESTDIR=$LFS</parameter>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/chapter05/glibc.xml:175
msgid ""
"The <envar>DESTDIR</envar> make variable is used by almost all packages to "
"define the location where the package should be installed. If it is not set, "
"it defaults to the root (<filename class=\"directory\">/</filename>) "
"directory. Here we specify that the package is installed in <filename "
"class=\"directory\"> $LFS</filename>, which will become the root directory "
"in <xref linkend= \"ch-tools-chroot\" role='.'/>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/chapter05/glibc.xml:187
msgid ""
"Fix a hard coded path to the executable loader in the <command>ldd</command> "
"script:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><screen>
#: en/chapter05/glibc.xml:190
#, no-wrap
msgid "<userinput remap=\"install\">sed '/RTLDLIST=/s@/usr@@g' -i $LFS/usr/bin/ldd</userinput>"
msgstr "<userinput remap=\"install\">sed '/RTLDLIST=/s@/usr@@g' -i $LFS/usr/bin/ldd</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/chapter05/glibc.xml:192
msgid ""
"Now that our cross toolchain is in place, it is important to ensure that "
"compiling and linking will work as expected. We do this by performing some "
"sanity checks:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><screen>
#: en/chapter05/glibc.xml:196
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<userinput>echo 'int main(){}' | $LFS_TGT-gcc -x c - -v -Wl,--verbose &amp;&gt; dummy.log\n"
"readelf -l a.out | grep ': /lib'</userinput>"
msgstr ""
"<userinput>echo 'int main(){}' | $LFS_TGT-gcc -x c - -v -Wl,--verbose &amp;&gt; dummy.log\n"
"readelf -l a.out | grep ': /lib'</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/chapter05/glibc.xml:199 en/chapter08/gcc.xml:254
msgid ""
"There should be no errors, and the output of the last command will be "
"(allowing for platform-specific differences in the dynamic linker name):"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><screen>
#: en/chapter05/glibc.xml:203 en/chapter08/gcc.xml:258
#, no-wrap
msgid "<computeroutput>[Requesting program interpreter: /lib64/ld-linux-x86-64.so.2]</computeroutput>"
msgstr "<computeroutput>[Requesting program interpreter: /lib64/ld-linux-x86-64.so.2]</computeroutput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/chapter05/glibc.xml:205
msgid ""
"Note that this path should not contain <filename class='directory'>/mnt/lfs</"
"filename> (or the value of the <envar>LFS</envar> variable if you used a "
"different one).  The path is resolved when the compiled program is executed, "
"and that should only happen after we enter the chroot environment where the "
"kernel would consider <filename class='directory'>$LFS</filename> as the "
"root directory (<filename class='directory'>/</filename>)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/chapter05/glibc.xml:213 en/chapter08/gcc.xml:260
msgid "Now make sure that we're set up to use the correct start files:"
msgstr "Now make sure that we're set up to use the correct start files:"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><screen>
#: en/chapter05/glibc.xml:215
#, no-wrap
msgid "<userinput>grep -E -o \"$LFS/lib.*/S?crt[1in].*succeeded\" dummy.log</userinput>"
msgstr "<userinput>grep -E -o \"$LFS/lib.*/S?crt[1in].*succeeded\" dummy.log</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/chapter05/glibc.xml:217 en/chapter05/glibc.xml:263
#: en/chapter08/gcc.xml:264 en/chapter08/gcc.xml:325
msgid "The output of the last command should be:"
msgstr "마지막 명령의 출력은 아래에:"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><screen>
#: en/chapter05/glibc.xml:219
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<computeroutput>/mnt/lfs/lib/../lib/Scrt1.o succeeded\n"
"/mnt/lfs/lib/../lib/crti.o succeeded\n"
"/mnt/lfs/lib/../lib/crtn.o succeeded</computeroutput>"
msgstr ""
"<computeroutput>/mnt/lfs/lib/../lib/Scrt1.o succeeded\n"
"/mnt/lfs/lib/../lib/crti.o succeeded\n"
"/mnt/lfs/lib/../lib/crtn.o succeeded</computeroutput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/chapter05/glibc.xml:223 en/chapter08/gcc.xml:277
msgid "Verify that the compiler is searching for the correct header files:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><screen>
#: en/chapter05/glibc.xml:226
#, no-wrap
msgid "<userinput>grep -B3 \"^ $LFS/usr/include\" dummy.log</userinput>"
msgstr "<userinput>grep -B3 \"^ $LFS/usr/include\" dummy.log</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/chapter05/glibc.xml:228 en/chapter08/gcc.xml:282
msgid "This command should return the following output:"
msgstr "이 명령은 다음 출력을 반환:"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><screen>
#: en/chapter05/glibc.xml:230
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<computeroutput>#include &lt;...&gt; search starts here:\n"
" /mnt/lfs/tools/lib/gcc/x86_64-lfs-linux-gnu/&gcc-version;/include\n"
" /mnt/lfs/tools/lib/gcc/x86_64-lfs-linux-gnu/&gcc-version;/include-fixed\n"
" /mnt/lfs/usr/include</computeroutput>"
msgstr ""
"<computeroutput>#include &lt;...&gt; search starts here:\n"
" /mnt/lfs/tools/lib/gcc/x86_64-lfs-linux-gnu/&gcc-version;/include\n"
" /mnt/lfs/tools/lib/gcc/x86_64-lfs-linux-gnu/&gcc-version;/include-fixed\n"
" /mnt/lfs/usr/include</computeroutput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/chapter05/glibc.xml:235 en/chapter08/gcc.xml:290
msgid ""
"Again, the directory named after your target triplet may be different than "
"the above, depending on your system architecture."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/chapter05/glibc.xml:238 en/chapter08/gcc.xml:293
msgid ""
"Next, verify that the new linker is being used with the correct search paths:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><screen>
#: en/chapter05/glibc.xml:240 en/chapter08/gcc.xml:295
#, no-wrap
msgid "<userinput>grep 'SEARCH.*/usr/lib' dummy.log |sed 's|; |\\n|g'</userinput>"
msgstr "<userinput>grep 'SEARCH.*/usr/lib' dummy.log |sed 's|; |\\n|g'</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/chapter05/glibc.xml:242 en/chapter08/gcc.xml:297
msgid ""
"References to paths that have components with '-linux-gnu' should be "
"ignored, but otherwise the output of the last command should be:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><screen>
#: en/chapter05/glibc.xml:245
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<computeroutput>SEARCH_DIR(\"=/mnt/lfs/tools/x86_64-lfs-linux-gnu/lib64\")\n"
"SEARCH_DIR(\"=/usr/local/lib64\")\n"
"SEARCH_DIR(\"=/lib64\")\n"
"SEARCH_DIR(\"=/usr/lib64\")\n"
"SEARCH_DIR(\"=/mnt/lfs/tools/x86_64-lfs-linux-gnu/lib\")\n"
"SEARCH_DIR(\"=/usr/local/lib\")\n"
"SEARCH_DIR(\"=/lib\")\n"
"SEARCH_DIR(\"=/usr/lib\");</computeroutput>"
msgstr ""
"<computeroutput>SEARCH_DIR(\"=/mnt/lfs/tools/x86_64-lfs-linux-gnu/lib64\")\n"
"SEARCH_DIR(\"=/usr/local/lib64\")\n"
"SEARCH_DIR(\"=/lib64\")\n"
"SEARCH_DIR(\"=/usr/lib64\")\n"
"SEARCH_DIR(\"=/mnt/lfs/tools/x86_64-lfs-linux-gnu/lib\")\n"
"SEARCH_DIR(\"=/usr/local/lib\")\n"
"SEARCH_DIR(\"=/lib\")\n"
"SEARCH_DIR(\"=/usr/lib\");</computeroutput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/chapter05/glibc.xml:254
msgid ""
"A 32-bit system may use a few other directories, but anyway the important "
"facet here is all the paths should begin with an equal sign (<literal>=</"
"literal>), which would be replaced with the sysroot directory that we've "
"configured for the linker."
msgstr ""
"A 32-bit system may use a few other directories, but anyway the important "
"facet here is all the paths should begin with an equal sign (<literal>=</"
"literal>), which would be replaced with the sysroot directory that we've "
"configured for the linker."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/chapter05/glibc.xml:259 en/chapter08/gcc.xml:321
msgid "Next make sure that we're using the correct libc:"
msgstr "Next make sure that we're using the correct libc:"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><screen>
#: en/chapter05/glibc.xml:261 en/chapter08/gcc.xml:323
#, no-wrap
msgid "<userinput>grep \"/lib.*/libc.so.6 \" dummy.log</userinput>"
msgstr "<userinput>grep \"/lib.*/libc.so.6 \" dummy.log</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><screen>
#: en/chapter05/glibc.xml:265
#, no-wrap
msgid "<computeroutput>attempt to open /mnt/lfs/usr/lib/libc.so.6 succeeded</computeroutput>"
msgstr "<computeroutput>attempt to open /mnt/lfs/usr/lib/libc.so.6 succeeded</computeroutput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/chapter05/glibc.xml:267 en/chapter08/gcc.xml:329
msgid "Make sure GCC is using the correct dynamic linker:"
msgstr "Make sure GCC is using the correct dynamic linker:"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><screen>
#: en/chapter05/glibc.xml:269 en/chapter08/gcc.xml:331
#, no-wrap
msgid "<userinput>grep found dummy.log</userinput>"
msgstr "<userinput>grep found dummy.log</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/chapter05/glibc.xml:271 en/chapter08/gcc.xml:333
msgid ""
"The output of the last command should be (allowing for platform-specific "
"differences in dynamic linker name):"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><screen>
#: en/chapter05/glibc.xml:274
#, no-wrap
msgid "<computeroutput>found ld-linux-x86-64.so.2 at /mnt/lfs/usr/lib/ld-linux-x86-64.so.2</computeroutput>"
msgstr "<computeroutput>found ld-linux-x86-64.so.2 at /mnt/lfs/usr/lib/ld-linux-x86-64.so.2</computeroutput>"

#. The most likely
#.   reason is that something went wrong with the specs file adjustment.
#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/chapter05/glibc.xml:276 en/chapter08/gcc.xml:338
msgid ""
"If the output does not appear as shown above or is not received at all, then "
"something is seriously wrong. Investigate and retrace the steps to find out "
"where the problem is and correct it.  Any issues should be resolved before "
"continuing with the process."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/chapter05/glibc.xml:281 en/chapter08/gcc.xml:344
msgid "Once everything is working correctly, clean up the test files:"
msgstr "모든 것이 올바르게 동작하면, 테스트 파일 깨끗이 지우기:"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><screen>
#: en/chapter05/glibc.xml:283 en/chapter08/gcc.xml:346
#, no-wrap
msgid "<userinput>rm -v a.out dummy.log</userinput>"
msgstr "<userinput>rm -v a.out dummy.log</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><note><para>
#: en/chapter05/glibc.xml:285
msgid ""
"Building the packages in the next chapter will serve as an additional check "
"that the toolchain has been built properly. If some package, especially "
"Binutils-pass2 or GCC-pass2, fails to build, it is an indication that "
"something has gone wrong with the preceding Binutils, GCC, or Glibc "
"installations."
msgstr ""
"다음 장에서 패키지들을 빌드하는 과정은 툴체인이 제대로 빌드되었는지 확인하는 "
"추가적인 점검 역할을 할 것입니다. 만약 특정 패키지, 특히 Binutils-pass2 또는 "
"GCC-pass2의 빌드에 실패한다면, 이는 이전에 진행한 Binutils, GCC, 또는 Glibc "
"설치 과정에서 무언가 잘못되었음을 나타내는 신호입니다."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/chapter05/glibc.xml:302
msgid ""
"Details on this package are located in <xref linkend=\"contents-glibc\" "
"role=\".\"/>"
msgstr "이 패키지 상세 정보 <xref linkend=\"contents-glibc\" role=\".\"/>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/chapter05/introduction.xml:13
msgid ""
"This chapter shows how to build a cross-compiler and its associated tools. "
"Although here cross-compilation is faked, the principles are the same as for "
"a real cross-toolchain."
msgstr ""
"이 장에서는 크로스 컴파일러와 그와 관련된 도구들을 빌드하는 방법을 보여줍니"
"다. 여기서는 크로스 컴파일을 가상으로 흉내 내어 진행하지만, 그 원리는 실제 크"
"로스 툴체인을 만드는 것과 동일합니다."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/chapter05/introduction.xml:17
msgid ""
"The programs compiled in this chapter will be installed under the <filename "
"class=\"directory\">$LFS/tools</filename> directory to keep them separate "
"from the files installed in the following chapters. The libraries, on the "
"other hand, are installed into their final place, since they pertain to the "
"system we want to build."
msgstr ""
"이 장에서 컴파일한 프로그램들은 <filename class=\"directory\">$LFS/tools</"
"filename> 디렉터리 아래에 설치해서, 다음 장들에서 설치할 파일들과 분리할 것입"
"니다. 반면, 라이브러리들은 우리가 구축하고자 하는 시스템에 속하므로 최종 위치"
"에 설치합니다."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect1info>
#: en/chapter05/libstdc++.xml:12
msgid ""
"<productname>gcc-libstdc++</productname> <productnumber>&gcc-version;</"
"productnumber> <placeholder type=\"address\" id=\"0\"/>"
msgstr ""
"<productname>gcc-libstdc++</productname> <productnumber>&gcc-version;</"
"productnumber> <placeholder type=\"address\" id=\"0\"/>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><title>
#: en/chapter05/libstdc++.xml:17
msgid "Libstdc++ from GCC-&gcc-version;"
msgstr "GCC-&gcc-version;용 Libstdc++"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><indexterm><secondary>
#: en/chapter05/libstdc++.xml:21
msgid "tools, libstdc++ pass 1"
msgstr "도구, libstdc++ 패스 1"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/chapter05/libstdc++.xml:27
msgid ""
"Libstdc++ is the standard C++ library. It is needed to compile C++ code "
"(part of GCC is written in C++), but we had to defer its installation when "
"we built <xref linkend=\"ch-tools-gcc-pass1\"/> because Libstdc++ depends on "
"Glibc, which was not yet available in the target directory."
msgstr ""
"Libstdc++은 표준 C++ 라이브러리입니다. C++ 코드를 컴파일하는 데 필요(GCC의 일"
"부도 C++로 작성)하지만, 앞서 <xref linkend=\"ch-tools-gcc-pass1\"/>을 빌드할 "
"때는 이 라이브러리 설치를 미뤄야만 했습니다. Libstdc++은 Glibc에 의존하는데, "
"대상 디렉터리에 Glibc가 준비되지 않았기 때문입니다."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><segmentedlist><seglistitem><seg>
#: en/chapter05/libstdc++.xml:40
msgid "&libstdcpp-tmpp1-sbu;"
msgstr "&libstdcpp-tmpp1-sbu;"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><segmentedlist><seglistitem><seg>
#: en/chapter05/libstdc++.xml:41
msgid "&libstdcpp-tmpp1-du;"
msgstr "&libstdcpp-tmpp1-du;"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><title>
#: en/chapter05/libstdc++.xml:48
msgid "Installation of Target Libstdc++"
msgstr "Target Libstdc++ 설치"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><note><para>
#: en/chapter05/libstdc++.xml:51
msgid ""
"<application>Libstdc++</application> is part of the GCC sources.  You should "
"first unpack the GCC tarball and change to the <filename>gcc-&gcc-version;</"
"filename> directory."
msgstr ""
"<application>Libstdc++</application> 는 GCC 소스의 일부입니다. 먼저 GCC 타르"
"볼의 압축을 풀고 <filename>gcc-&gcc-version;</filename> 디렉터리로 옮기시오."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/chapter05/libstdc++.xml:56
msgid "Create a separate build directory for Libstdc++ and enter it:"
msgstr "Libstdc++을 위한 별도의 빌드 디렉터리를 만들고 그리로 이동:"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/chapter05/libstdc++.xml:61
msgid "Prepare Libstdc++ for compilation:"
msgstr "Libstdc++ 컴파일 준비하기:"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><screen>
#: en/chapter05/libstdc++.xml:63
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<userinput remap=\"configure\">../libstdc++-v3/configure      \\\n"
"    --host=$LFS_TGT            \\\n"
"    --build=$(../config.guess) \\\n"
"    --prefix=/usr              \\\n"
"    --disable-multilib         \\\n"
"    --disable-nls              \\\n"
"    --disable-libstdcxx-pch    \\\n"
"    --with-gxx-include-dir=/tools/$LFS_TGT/include/c++/&gcc-version;</userinput>"
msgstr ""
"<userinput remap=\"configure\">../libstdc++-v3/configure      \\\n"
"    --host=$LFS_TGT            \\\n"
"    --build=$(../config.guess) \\\n"
"    --prefix=/usr              \\\n"
"    --disable-multilib         \\\n"
"    --disable-nls              \\\n"
"    --disable-libstdcxx-pch    \\\n"
"    --with-gxx-include-dir=/tools/$LFS_TGT/include/c++/&gcc-version;</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/chapter05/libstdc++.xml:76
msgid "<parameter>--host=...</parameter>"
msgstr "<parameter>--host=...</parameter>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/chapter05/libstdc++.xml:78
msgid ""
"Specifies that the cross-compiler we have just built should be used instead "
"of the one in <filename>/usr/bin</filename>."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/chapter05/libstdc++.xml:85
msgid "<parameter>--disable-libstdcxx-pch</parameter>"
msgstr "<parameter>--disable-libstdcxx-pch</parameter>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/chapter05/libstdc++.xml:87
msgid ""
"This switch prevents the installation of precompiled include files, which "
"are not needed at this stage."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/chapter05/libstdc++.xml:93
msgid ""
"<parameter>--with-gxx-include-dir=/tools/$LFS_TGT/include/c++/&gcc-version;</"
"parameter>"
msgstr ""
"<parameter>--with-gxx-include-dir=/tools/$LFS_TGT/include/c++/&gcc-version;</"
"parameter>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/chapter05/libstdc++.xml:95
msgid ""
"This specifies the installation directory for include files.  Because "
"Libstdc++ is the standard C++ library for LFS, this directory should match "
"the location where the C++ compiler (<command>$LFS_TGT-g++</command>) would "
"search for the standard C++ include files. In a normal build, this "
"information is automatically passed to the Libstdc++ <command>configure</"
"command> options from the top level directory. In our case, this information "
"must be explicitly given.  The C++ compiler will prepend the sysroot path "
"<filename class=\"directory\">$LFS</filename> (specified when building GCC-"
"pass1) to the include file search path, so it will actually search in "
"<filename class=\"directory\">$LFS/tools/$LFS_TGT/include/c++/&gcc-version;</"
"filename>.  The combination of the <parameter>DESTDIR</parameter> variable "
"(in the <command>make install</command> command below)  and this switch "
"causes the headers to be installed there."
msgstr ""
"이 설정은 헤더 파일(include files)이 설치될 디렉터리를 지정합니다. Libstdc+"
"+은 LFS의 표준 C++ 라이브러리이므로, 이 디렉터리는 C++ 컴파일러"
"(<command>$LFS_TGT-g++</command>) 가 표준 C++ 헤더 파일을 찾는 위치와 일치해"
"야 합니다. 일반적인 빌드의 경우, 이 정보는 상위 디렉터리에서 Libstdc++ "
"<command>configure</command> 옵션으로 자동 전달됩니다. 우리 경우, 이 정보를 "
"명시적으로 지정해야 합니다. C++ 컴파일러는 (GCC Pass 1을 빌드할 때 지정했던) "
"시스템 루트(sysroot) 경로 <filename class=\"directory\">$LFS</filename> 를 헤"
"더 파일 탐색 경로 앞에 붙이므로, 실제로는 <filename class=\"directory\">$LFS/"
"tools/$LFS_TGT/include/c++/&gcc-version;</filename> 에서 파일을 찾습니다. (아"
"래 <command>make install</command> 명령에 사용되는) <parameter>DESTDIR</"
"parameter> 변수와 이 스위치를 조합하면 헤더 파일들이 해당 위치에 설치됩니다."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/chapter05/libstdc++.xml:116
msgid "Compile Libstdc++ by running:"
msgstr "Libstdc++을 컴파일하려면 실행:"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/chapter05/libstdc++.xml:120
msgid "Install the library:"
msgstr "라이브러리 설치:"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/chapter05/libstdc++.xml:124
msgid ""
"Remove the libtool archive files because they are harmful for cross-"
"compilation:"
msgstr "크로스 컴파일에 해로울 수 있는 libtool 아카이브 파일 제거:"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><screen>
#: en/chapter05/libstdc++.xml:127
#, no-wrap
msgid "<userinput remap=\"install\">rm -v $LFS/usr/lib/lib{stdc++{,exp,fs},supc++}.la</userinput>"
msgstr "<userinput remap=\"install\">rm -v $LFS/usr/lib/lib{stdc++{,exp,fs},supc++}.la</userinput>"

