#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><title>
#: en/chapter07/gettext.xml:44 en/chapter08/gettext.xml:44
msgid "Installation of Gettext"
msgstr "Gettext 설치"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/chapter07/gettext.xml:51
msgid ""
"For our temporary set of tools, we only need to install three programs from "
"Gettext."
msgstr ""
"우리 임시 도구 모음의 경우, Gettext에서 프로그램 3개만 설치하면 됩니다."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/chapter07/gettext.xml:54 en/chapter08/gettext.xml:51
msgid "Prepare Gettext for compilation:"
msgstr "Gettext 컴파일 준비하기:"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><screen>
#: en/chapter07/gettext.xml:56
#, no-wrap
msgid "<userinput remap=\"configure\">./configure --disable-shared</userinput>"
msgstr "<userinput remap=\"configure\">./configure --disable-shared</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><variablelist><title>
#: en/chapter07/gettext.xml:59 en/chapter07/python.xml:61
#: en/chapter08/gdbm.xml:58 en/chapter08/kbd.xml:66 en/chapter08/libffi.xml:71
#: en/chapter08/procps.xml:59 en/chapter08/tar.xml:52
msgid "The meaning of the configure option:"
msgstr "configure 옵션 뜻:"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/chapter07/gettext.xml:64
msgid ""
"We do not need to install any of the shared Gettext libraries at this time, "
"therefore there is no need to build them."
msgstr ""
"현재는 공유 Gettext 라이브러리를 설치할 필요가 없으므로, 이를 빌드할 필요가 "
"없습니다."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/chapter07/gettext.xml:75
msgid ""
"Install the <command>msgfmt</command>, <command>msgmerge</command>, and "
"<command>xgettext</command> programs:"
msgstr ""
"<command>msgfmt</command>, <command>msgmerge</command> 및 <command>xgettext</"
"command> 프로그램을 설치:"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><screen>
#: en/chapter07/gettext.xml:78
#, no-wrap
msgid "<userinput remap=\"install\">cp -v gettext-tools/src/{msgfmt,msgmerge,xgettext} /usr/bin</userinput>"
msgstr "<userinput remap=\"install\">cp -v gettext-tools/src/{msgfmt,msgmerge,xgettext} /usr/bin</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/chapter07/gettext.xml:85
msgid ""
"Details on this package are located in <xref linkend=\"contents-gettext\" "
"role=\".\"/>"
msgstr "이 패키지 상세 정보 <xref linkend=\"contents-gettext\" role=\".\"/>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/chapter07/introduction.xml:13
msgid ""
"This chapter shows how to build the last missing bits of the temporary "
"system: the tools needed to build the various packages.  Now that all "
"circular dependencies have been resolved, a <quote>chroot</quote> "
"environment, completely isolated from the host operating system (except for "
"the running kernel), can be used for the build."
msgstr ""
"이 장에서는 임시 시스템에서 마지막으로 빠진 부분들, 즉 다양한 패키지를 빌드하"
"는 데 필요한 도구들을 빌드하는 방법을 보여줍니다. 이제 순환 의존성(circular "
"dependencies)이 모두 해결되었으므로, 호스트 운영 체제로부터 (실행 중인 커널"
"을 제외하고) 완전히 격리된 <quote>chroot</quote> 환경을 빌드에 사용할 수 있습"
"니다."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/chapter07/introduction.xml:19
msgid ""
"For proper operation of the isolated environment, some communication with "
"the running kernel must be established. This is done via the so-called "
"<emphasis>Virtual Kernel File Systems</emphasis>, which will be mounted "
"before entering the chroot environment. You may want to verify that they are "
"mounted by issuing the <command>findmnt</command> command."
msgstr ""
"격리된 환경이 적절히 작동하려면 실행 중인 커널과의 통신이 반드시 이루어져야 "
"합니다. 이는 chroot 환경에 진입하기 전에 마운트할 소위 <emphasis>가상 커널 파"
"일 시스템(Virtual Kernel File Systems)</emphasis>을 통해 수행됩니다. "
"<command>findmnt</command> 명령을 실행하여 이들이 제대로 마운트되었는지 확인"
"해 보는 것이 좋습니다."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/chapter07/introduction.xml:25
msgid ""
"Until <xref linkend=\"ch-tools-chroot\"/>, the commands must be run as "
"<systemitem class=\"username\">root</systemitem>, with the <envar>LFS</"
"envar> variable set. After entering chroot, all commands are run as &root;, "
"fortunately without access to the OS of the computer you built LFS on. Be "
"careful anyway, as it is easy to destroy the whole LFS system with bad "
"commands."
msgstr ""
"<xref linkend=\"ch-tools-chroot\"/> 전까지 모든 명령은 <envar>LFS</envar> 변"
"수가 설정된 상태에서 <systemitem class=\"username\">root</systemitem> 사용자"
"로 실행해야 합니다. chroot에 진입한 후에는 모든 명령이 그대로 root로 실행되지"
"만, 다행히 LFS를 빌드하고 있는 호스트 컴퓨터의 운영체제에는 접근할 수 없습니"
"다. 언제나 주의하십시오. 왜냐하면 잘못된 명령으로 LFS 시스템 전체를 파괴하기 "
"쉽기 때문."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><title>
#: en/chapter07/kernfs.xml:11
msgid "Preparing Virtual Kernel File Systems"
msgstr "가상 커널 파일 시스템 준비"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><indexterm><primary>
#: en/chapter07/kernfs.xml:14
msgid "/dev/*"
msgstr "/dev/*"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/chapter07/kernfs.xml:17
msgid ""
"Applications running in userspace utilize various file systems created by "
"the kernel to communicate with the kernel itself. These file systems are "
"virtual: no disk space is used for them. The content of these file systems "
"resides in memory. These file systems must be mounted in the $LFS directory "
"tree so the applications can find them in the chroot environment."
msgstr ""
"사용자 공간에서 실행되는 애플리케이션들은 커널과 통신하기 위해 커널이 생성한 "
"다양한 파일 시스템을 활용합니다. 이 파일 시스템들은 가상 파일 시스템으로, 디"
"스크 공간을 쓰지 않습니다. 이 파일 시스템의 내용은 메모리에 상주합니다. 애플"
"리케이션들이 chroot 환경 내에서 이들을 찾을 수 있도록, 이 파일 시스템들을 "
"$LFS 디렉터리 트리 안에 마운트해야 합니다."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/chapter07/kernfs.xml:24
msgid ""
"Begin by creating the directories on which these virtual file systems will "
"be mounted:"
msgstr "이 가상 파일 시스템들이 마운트될 디렉터리들을 생성하는 것으로 시작:"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><screen>
#: en/chapter07/kernfs.xml:27
#, no-wrap
msgid "<userinput>mkdir -pv $LFS/{dev,proc,sys,run}</userinput>"
msgstr "<userinput>mkdir -pv $LFS/{dev,proc,sys,run}</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><title>
#: en/chapter07/kernfs.xml:30
msgid "Mounting and Populating /dev"
msgstr "Mounting 및 Populating /dev"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/chapter07/kernfs.xml:32
msgid ""
"During a normal boot of an LFS system, the kernel automatically mounts the "
"<systemitem class=\"filesystem\">devtmpfs</systemitem> file system on the "
"<filename class=\"directory\">/dev</filename> directory; the kernel creates "
"device nodes on that virtual file system during the boot process, or when a "
"device is first detected or accessed. The udev daemon may change the "
"ownership or permissions of the device nodes created by the kernel, and "
"create new device nodes or symlinks, to ease the work of distro maintainers "
"and system administrators.  (See <xref linkend='ch-config-udev-device-node-"
"creation'/> for details.)  If the host kernel supports &devtmpfs;, we can "
"simply mount a &devtmpfs; at <filename class='directory'>$LFS/dev</filename> "
"and rely on the kernel to populate it."
msgstr ""
"LFS 시스템의 일반적인 부팅 과정 중에, 커널은 <systemitem "
"class=\"filesystem\">devtmpfs</systemitem> 파일 시스템을 자동으로 <filename "
"class=\"directory\">/dev</filename> 디렉터리에 마운트합니다. 커널은 부팅 과"
"정 중이나 장치가 처음 감지되거나 접근될 때, 해당 가상 파일 시스템에 장치 노드"
"들을 생성합니다. udev 데몬은 배포판 유지 관리자와 시스템 관리자의 작업을 돕"
"기 위해 커널이 생성한 장치 노드의 소유권이나 권한을 변경할 수 있으며, 새로운 "
"장치 노드나 심볼릭 링크를 생성할 수도 있습니다. (자세한 내용은 <xref "
"linkend='ch-config-udev-device-node-creation'/>를 참조하십시오.) 만약 호스트 "
"커널이 &devtmpfs;를 지원한다면, 우리는 단순히 <filename "
"class='directory'>$LFS/dev</filename>에 &devtmpfs; 를 마운트하고 커널이 그 내"
"용을 채우도록 맡길 수 있습니다."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/chapter07/kernfs.xml:46
msgid ""
"But some host kernels lack &devtmpfs; support; these host distros use "
"different methods to create the content of <filename class=\"directory\">/"
"dev</filename>.  So the only host-agnostic way to populate the <filename "
"class=\"directory\">$LFS/dev</filename> directory is by bind mounting the "
"host system's <filename class=\"directory\">/dev</filename> directory. A "
"bind mount is a special type of mount that makes a directory subtree or a "
"file visible at some other location. Use the following command to do this."
msgstr ""
"그러나 일부 호스트 커널은 &devtmpfs; 지원이 부족하며, 이러한 호스트 배포판들"
"은 <filename class=\"directory\">/dev</filename>의 내용을 생성하기 위해 다른 "
"방법들을 사용합니다. 따라서 호스트 종류에 상관없이 <filename "
"class=\"directory\">$LFS/dev</filename> 디렉터리를 채울 수 있는 유일한 방법"
"은 호스트 시스템의 <filename class=\"directory\">/dev</filename> 디렉터리를 "
"바인드 마운트(bind mount)하는 것입니다. 바인드 마운트는 디렉터리 하위 트리나 "
"파일을 다른 위치에서 볼 수 있게 해주는 특별한 유형의 마운트입니다. 이를 위해 "
"다음 명령을 사용하십시오."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><screen>
#: en/chapter07/kernfs.xml:57
#, no-wrap
msgid "<userinput>mount -v --bind /dev $LFS/dev</userinput>"
msgstr "<userinput>mount -v --bind /dev $LFS/dev</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><title>
#: en/chapter07/kernfs.xml:62
msgid "Mounting Virtual Kernel File Systems"
msgstr "Mounting Virtual Kernel File Systems"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/chapter07/kernfs.xml:64
msgid "Now mount the remaining virtual kernel file systems:"
msgstr "Now mount the remaining virtual kernel file systems:"

#.  Do not put any option after $LFS/${mountpoint} or jhalfs cannot
#.            handle it! 
#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><screen>
#: en/chapter07/kernfs.xml:69
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<userinput>mount -vt devpts devpts -o gid=5,mode=0620 $LFS/dev/pts\n"
"mount -vt proc proc $LFS/proc\n"
"mount -vt sysfs sysfs $LFS/sys\n"
"mount -vt tmpfs tmpfs $LFS/run</userinput>"
msgstr ""
"<userinput>mount -vt devpts devpts -o gid=5,mode=0620 $LFS/dev/pts\n"
"mount -vt proc proc $LFS/proc\n"
"mount -vt sysfs sysfs $LFS/sys\n"
"mount -vt tmpfs tmpfs $LFS/run</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><variablelist><title>
#: en/chapter07/kernfs.xml:75
msgid "The meaning of the mount options for devpts:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/chapter07/kernfs.xml:78
msgid "<parameter>gid=5</parameter>"
msgstr "<parameter>gid=5</parameter>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/chapter07/kernfs.xml:80
msgid ""
"This ensures that all devpts-created device nodes are owned by group ID 5.  "
"This is the ID we will use later on for the <systemitem "
"class=\"groupname\">tty</systemitem> group.  We use the group ID instead of "
"a name, since the host system might use a different ID for its <systemitem "
"class=\"groupname\">tty</systemitem> group."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/chapter07/kernfs.xml:89
msgid "<parameter>mode=0620</parameter>"
msgstr "<parameter>mode=0620</parameter>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/chapter07/kernfs.xml:91
msgid ""
"This ensures that all devpts-created device nodes have mode 0620 (user "
"readable and writable, group writable).  Together with the option above, "
"this ensures that devpts will create device nodes that meet the requirements "
"of grantpt(), meaning the Glibc <command>pt_chown</command> helper binary "
"(which is not installed by default) is not necessary."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/chapter07/kernfs.xml:102
msgid ""
"In some host systems, <filename>/dev/shm</filename> is a symbolic link to a "
"directory, typically <filename class=\"directory\">/run/shm</filename>.  "
"The /run tmpfs was mounted above so in this case only a directory needs to "
"be created with the correct permissions."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/chapter07/kernfs.xml:108
msgid ""
"In other host systems <filename>/dev/shm</filename> is a mount point for a "
"tmpfs. In that case the mount of /dev above will only create /dev/shm as a "
"directory in the chroot environment. In this situation we must explicitly "
"mount a tmpfs:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><screen>
#: en/chapter07/kernfs.xml:113
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<userinput>if [ -h $LFS/dev/shm ]; then\n"
"  install -v -d -m 1777 $LFS$(realpath /dev/shm)\n"
"else\n"
"  mount -vt tmpfs -o nosuid,nodev tmpfs $LFS/dev/shm\n"
"fi</userinput>"
msgstr ""
"<userinput>if [ -h $LFS/dev/shm ]; then\n"
"  install -v -d -m 1777 $LFS$(realpath /dev/shm)\n"
"else\n"
"  mount -vt tmpfs -o nosuid,nodev tmpfs $LFS/dev/shm\n"
"fi</userinput>"

