#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/chapter08/glibc.xml:26
msgid ""
"The Glibc package contains the main C library. This library provides the "
"basic routines for allocating memory, searching directories, opening and "
"closing files, reading and writing files, string handling, pattern matching, "
"arithmetic, and so on."
msgstr ""
"Glibc 패키지에는 주 C 라이브러리가 들어 있습니다. Glibc 라이브러리는 메모리 "
"할당, 디렉터리 검색, 파일 열기 및 닫기, 파일 읽기 및 쓰기, 문자열 처리, 패턴 "
"일치, 산술 연산 등 기본적인 루틴을 제공합니다."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><segmentedlist><seglistitem><seg>
#: en/chapter08/glibc.xml:36
msgid "&glibc-fin-sbu;"
msgstr "&glibc-fin-sbu;"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><segmentedlist><seglistitem><seg>
#: en/chapter08/glibc.xml:37
msgid "&glibc-fin-du;"
msgstr "&glibc-fin-du;"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/chapter08/glibc.xml:50
msgid ""
"Some of the Glibc programs use the non-FHS compliant <filename "
"class=\"directory\">/var/db</filename> directory to store their runtime "
"data. Apply the following patch to make such programs store their runtime "
"data in the FHS-compliant locations:"
msgstr ""
"일부 Glibc 프로그램은 FHS를 준수하지 않는 <filename class=\"directory\">/var/"
"db</filename> 디렉터리를 사용하여 런타임 데이터를 저장합니다. 이러한 프로그램"
"이 FHS를 준수하는 위치에 런타임 데이터를 저장하도록 다음 패치를 적용:"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/chapter08/glibc.xml:71
msgid ""
"Ensure that the <command>ldconfig</command> and <command>sln</command> "
"utilities will be installed into <filename class=\"directory\">/usr/sbin</"
"filename>:"
msgstr ""
"<command>ldconfig</command> 및 <command>sln</command> 유틸리티가 <filename "
"class=\"directory\">/usr/sbin</filename> 디렉터리에 설치되도록 확인:"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/chapter08/glibc.xml:77
msgid "Prepare Glibc for compilation:"
msgstr "Glibc 컴파일 준비하기:"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><screen>
#: en/chapter08/glibc.xml:79
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<userinput remap=\"configure\">../configure --prefix=/usr                   \\\n"
"             --disable-werror                \\\n"
"             --disable-nscd                  \\\n"
"             libc_cv_slibdir=/usr/lib        \\\n"
"             --enable-stack-protector=strong \\\n"
"             --enable-kernel=&min-kernel;</userinput>"
msgstr ""
"<userinput remap=\"configure\">../configure --prefix=/usr                   \\\n"
"             --disable-werror                \\\n"
"             --disable-nscd                  \\\n"
"             libc_cv_slibdir=/usr/lib        \\\n"
"             --enable-stack-protector=strong \\\n"
"             --enable-kernel=&min-kernel;</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/chapter08/glibc.xml:92
msgid ""
"This option disables the -Werror option passed to GCC.  This is necessary "
"for running the test suite."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/chapter08/glibc.xml:100
msgid ""
"This option tells the build system that this Glibc may be used with kernels "
"as old as &min-kernel;. This means generating workarounds in case a system "
"call introduced in a later version cannot be used."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/chapter08/glibc.xml:108
msgid "<parameter>--enable-stack-protector=strong</parameter>"
msgstr "<parameter>--enable-stack-protector=strong</parameter>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/chapter08/glibc.xml:110
msgid ""
"This option increases system security by adding extra code to check for "
"buffer overflows, such as stack smashing attacks.  Note that Glibc always "
"explicitly overrides the default of GCC, so this option is still needed even "
"though we've already specified <option>--enable-default-ssp</option> for GCC."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/chapter08/glibc.xml:130
msgid ""
"This variable sets the correct library for all systems.  We do not want "
"lib64 to be used."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><important><para>
#: en/chapter08/glibc.xml:142
msgid ""
"In this section, the test suite for Glibc is considered critical.  Do not "
"skip it under any circumstance."
msgstr ""
"이 섹션에서 Glibc의 테스트 스위트(test suite)는 매우 중요한 과정으로 간주됩니"
"다. 어떤 상황에서도 이 단계를 건너뛰지 마십시오."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/chapter08/glibc.xml:146
msgid ""
"Generally a few tests do not pass. The test failures listed below are "
"usually safe to ignore."
msgstr ""
"일반적으로 몇 가지 테스트는 통과하지 못할 수도 있습니다. 아래에 나열된 테스"
"트 실패 항목들은 무시해도 대개 안전합니다."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/chapter08/glibc.xml:161
msgid ""
"You may see some test failures. The Glibc test suite is somewhat dependent "
"on the host system. A few failures out of over 6000 tests can generally be "
"ignored. This is a list of the most common issues seen for recent versions "
"of LFS:"
msgstr ""
"일부 테스트 실패할 수 있습니다. Glibc 테스트 스위트는 어느 정도 호스트 시스템"
"의 환경에 의존적입니다. 6,000개 넘는 테스트 중 몇 가지 실패는 대개 무시할 수 "
"있습니다. 최근 버전 LFS에서 가장 흔히 발견되는 문제의 목록:"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/chapter08/glibc.xml:169
msgid ""
"<emphasis>io/tst-lchmod</emphasis> is known to fail in the LFS chroot "
"environment."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/chapter08/glibc.xml:183
msgid ""
"Some tests, for example <emphasis>nss/tst-nss-files-hosts-multi</emphasis> "
"and <emphasis>nptl/tst-thread-affinity*</emphasis> are known to fail due to "
"a timeout (especially when the system is relatively slow and/or running the "
"test suite with multiple parallel make jobs).  These tests can be identified "
"with:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><itemizedlist><listitem><screen>
#: en/chapter08/glibc.xml:190
#, no-wrap
msgid "<userinput remap=\"test\">grep \"Timed out\" $(find -name \\*.out)</userinput>"
msgstr "<userinput remap=\"test\">grep \"Timed out\" $(find -name \\*.out)</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/chapter08/glibc.xml:192
msgid ""
"It's possible to re-run a single test with enlarged timeout with "
"<command>TIMEOUTFACTOR=<replaceable>&lt;factor&gt;</replaceable> make test "
"t=<replaceable>&lt;test name&gt;</replaceable></command>.  For example, "
"<command>TIMEOUTFACTOR=10 make test t=nss/tst-nss-files-hosts-multi</"
"command> will re-run <emphasis>nss/tst-nss-files-hosts-multi</emphasis> with "
"ten times the original timeout."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/chapter08/glibc.xml:203
msgid ""
"Additionally, some tests may fail with a relatively old CPU model (for "
"example <emphasis>elf/tst-cpu-features-cpuinfo</emphasis>) or host kernel "
"version (for example <emphasis>stdlib/tst-arc4random-thread</emphasis>)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/chapter08/glibc.xml:211
msgid ""
"Though it is a harmless message, the install stage of Glibc will complain "
"about the absence of <filename>/etc/ld.so.conf</filename>.  Prevent this "
"warning with:"
msgstr ""
"비록 무해한 메시지이긴 하지만, Glibc 설치 단계에서 <filename>/etc/"
"ld.so.conf</filename> 파일이 없다고 불평할 것입니다. 이 경고를 막으려면:"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><screen>
#: en/chapter08/glibc.xml:215
#, no-wrap
msgid "<userinput remap=\"install\">touch /etc/ld.so.conf</userinput>"
msgstr "<userinput remap=\"install\">touch /etc/ld.so.conf</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/chapter08/glibc.xml:218
msgid ""
"Fix the Makefile to skip an outdated sanity check that fails with a modern "
"Glibc configuration:"
msgstr ""
"최신 Glibc 설정에서 실패하는 오래된 무결성 검사(sanity check)를 건너뛰도록 "
"Makefile을 수정:"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><screen>
#: en/chapter08/glibc.xml:221
#, no-wrap
msgid "<userinput remap=\"install\">sed '/test-installation/s@$(PERL)@echo not running@' -i ../Makefile</userinput>"
msgstr "<userinput remap=\"install\">sed '/test-installation/s@$(PERL)@echo not running@' -i ../Makefile</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><important><para>
#: en/chapter08/glibc.xml:225
msgid ""
"If upgrading Glibc to a new minor version (for example, from Glibc-2.36 to "
"Glibc-&glibc-version;) on a running LFS system, you need to take some extra "
"precautions to avoid breaking the system:"
msgstr ""
"실행 중인 LFS 시스템에서 Glibc를 새로운 마이너 버전으로 업그레이드할 경우"
"(예: Glibc-2.36에서 Glibc-&glibc-version; 으로), 시스템이 망가지는 것을 막기 "
"위해 지켜야할 몇 가지 추가적인 주의 사항:"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><important><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/chapter08/glibc.xml:241
msgid ""
"Upgrading Glibc on a LFS system prior to 11.0 (exclusive) is not supported.  "
"Rebuild LFS if you are running such an old LFS system but you need a newer "
"Glibc."
msgstr ""
"11.0 미만(11.0 제외)의 LFS 시스템에서 Glibc를 업그레이드하는 것은 지원되지 않"
"습니다. 만약 이처럼 오래된 LFS 시스템을 사용 중인데 더 새로운 Glibc가 필요하"
"다면, LFS를 처음부터 다시 빌드하십시오."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><important><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/chapter08/glibc.xml:250
msgid ""
"If upgrading on a LFS system prior to 12.0 (exclusive), install "
"<application>Libxcrypt</application> following <xref role='.' linkend='ch-"
"system-libxcrypt'/> In addition to a normal <application>Libxcrypt</"
"application> installation, <emphasis role='bold'>you MUST follow the note in "
"Libxcrypt section to install <filename class='libraryfile'>libcrypt.so.1*</"
"filename> (replacing <filename class='libraryfile'>libcrypt.so.1</filename> "
"from the prior Glibc installation)</emphasis>."
msgstr ""
"12.0 미만(12.0 제외)의 LFS 시스템에서 업그레이드하는 경우, <xref role='.' "
"linkend='ch-system-libxcrypt'/> 참고하여 <application>Libxcrypt</"
"application> 을 설치하십시오. 일반적인 <application>Libxcrypt</application> "
"설치 외에도, <emphasis role='bold'>반드시 Libxcrypt 섹션의 노트를 따라 "
"<filename class='libraryfile'>libcrypt.so.1</filename>을 설치해야 합니다(기"
"존 Glibc 설치로 생성된 <filename class='libraryfile'>libcrypt.so.1</filename>"
"을 대체하게 됩니다)</emphasis>."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><important><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/chapter08/glibc.xml:269
msgid ""
"If upgrading on a LFS system prior to 12.1 (exclusive), remove the "
"<command>nscd</command> program:"
msgstr ""
"12.1 미만(12.1 제외)의 LFS 시스템에서 업그레이드하는 경우, <command>nscd</"
"command> 프로그램을 제거:"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><important><itemizedlist><listitem><screen>
#: en/chapter08/glibc.xml:273
#, no-wrap
msgid "<userinput>rm -f /usr/sbin/nscd</userinput>"
msgstr "<userinput>rm -f /usr/sbin/nscd</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><important><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/chapter08/glibc.xml:276
msgid ""
"If this system (prior to LFS 12.1, exclusive) is based on Systemd, it's also "
"needed to disable and stop the <command>nscd</command> service now:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><important><itemizedlist><listitem><screen>
#: en/chapter08/glibc.xml:281
#, no-wrap
msgid "<userinput>systemctl disable --now nscd</userinput>"
msgstr "<userinput>systemctl disable --now nscd</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><important><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/chapter08/glibc.xml:286
msgid ""
"Upgrade the kernel and reboot if it's older than &min-kernel; (check the "
"current version with <command>uname -r</command>)  or if you want to upgrade "
"it anyway, following <xref linkend='ch-bootable-kernel' role='.'/>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><important><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/chapter08/glibc.xml:295
msgid ""
"Upgrade the kernel API headers if it's older than &min-kernel; (check the "
"current version with <command>cat /usr/include/linux/version.h</command>)  "
"or if you want to upgrade it anyway, following <xref linkend='ch-tools-linux-"
"headers'/> (but removing <envar>$LFS</envar> from the <command>cp</command> "
"command)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><important><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/chapter08/glibc.xml:313
msgid ""
"Perform a <envar>DESTDIR</envar> installation and upgrade the Glibc shared "
"libraries on the system using one single <command>install</command> command:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><important><itemizedlist><listitem><screen>
#: en/chapter08/glibc.xml:318
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<userinput>make DESTDIR=$PWD/dest install\n"
"install -vm755 dest/usr/lib/*.so.* /usr/lib</userinput>"
msgstr ""
"<userinput>make DESTDIR=$PWD/dest install\n"
"install -vm755 dest/usr/lib/*.so.* /usr/lib</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><important><para>
#: en/chapter08/glibc.xml:324
msgid ""
"It's imperative to strictly follow these steps above unless you completely "
"understand what you are doing.  <emphasis role='bold'>Any unexpected "
"deviation may render the system completely unusable.  YOU ARE WARNED.</"
"emphasis>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><important><para>
#: en/chapter08/glibc.xml:331
msgid ""
"Then continue to run the <command>make install</command> command, the "
"<command>sed</command> command against <filename>/usr/bin/ldd</filename>, "
"and the commands to install the locales.  Once they are finished, reboot the "
"system immediately."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><important><para>
#: en/chapter08/glibc.xml:339
msgid ""
"When the system has successfully rebooted, if you are running a LFS system "
"prior to 12.0 (exclusive) where GCC was not built with the <parameter>--"
"disable-fixincludes</parameter> option, move two GCC headers into a better "
"location and remove the stale <quote>fixed</quote> copies of the Glibc "
"headers:"
msgstr ""
"시스템이 성공적으로 재부팅된 후, 만약 <parameter>--disable-fixincludes</"
"parameter> 옵션 없이 GCC가 빌드된 12.0 미만(12.0 제외)의 LFS 시스템을 실행 중"
"이라면, 두 개의 GCC 헤더를 더 적절한 위치로 이동시키고 더 이상 유효하지 않은"
"(stale) <quote>수정된(fixed)</quote> Glibc 헤더 복사본을 제거:"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><important><screen>
#: en/chapter08/glibc.xml:346
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<userinput>DIR=$(dirname $(gcc -print-libgcc-file-name))\n"
"[ -e $DIR/include/limits.h ]    || mv $DIR/include{-fixed,}/limits.h\n"
"[ -e $DIR/include/syslimits.h ] || mv $DIR/include{-fixed,}/syslimits.h\n"
"rm -rfv $DIR/include-fixed/*\n"
"unset DIR</userinput>"
msgstr ""
"<userinput>DIR=$(dirname $(gcc -print-libgcc-file-name))\n"
"[ -e $DIR/include/limits.h ]    || mv $DIR/include{-fixed,}/limits.h\n"
"[ -e $DIR/include/syslimits.h ] || mv $DIR/include{-fixed,}/syslimits.h\n"
"rm -rfv $DIR/include-fixed/*\n"
"unset DIR</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/chapter08/glibc.xml:357
msgid ""
"Fix a hardcoded path to the executable loader in the <command>ldd</command> "
"script:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><screen>
#: en/chapter08/glibc.xml:360
#, no-wrap
msgid "<userinput remap=\"install\">sed '/RTLDLIST=/s@/usr@@g' -i /usr/bin/ldd</userinput>"
msgstr "<userinput remap=\"install\">sed '/RTLDLIST=/s@/usr@@g' -i /usr/bin/ldd</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/chapter08/glibc.xml:374
msgid ""
"Next, install the locales that can make the system respond in a different "
"language.  None of these locales are required, but if some of them are "
"missing, the test suites of some packages will skip important test cases."
msgstr ""
"Next, install the locales that can make the system respond in a different "
"language.  None of these locales are required, but if some of them are "
"missing, the test suites of some packages will skip important test cases."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/chapter08/glibc.xml:379
msgid ""
"Individual locales can be installed using the <command>localedef</command> "
"program. E.g., the second <command>localedef</command> command below "
"combines the <filename>/usr/share/i18n/locales/cs_CZ</filename> charset-"
"independent locale definition with the <filename>/usr/share/i18n/charmaps/"
"UTF-8.gz</filename> charmap definition and appends the result to the "
"<filename>/usr/lib/locale/locale-archive</filename> file.  The following "
"instructions will install the minimum set of locales necessary for the "
"optimal coverage of tests:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><screen>
#: en/chapter08/glibc.xml:390
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<userinput remap=\"locale-test\">localedef -i C -f UTF-8 C.UTF-8\n"
"localedef -i cs_CZ -f UTF-8 cs_CZ.UTF-8\n"
"localedef -i de_DE -f ISO-8859-1 de_DE\n"
"localedef -i de_DE@euro -f ISO-8859-15 de_DE@euro\n"
"localedef -i de_DE -f UTF-8 de_DE.UTF-8\n"
"localedef -i el_GR -f ISO-8859-7 el_GR\n"
"localedef -i en_GB -f ISO-8859-1 en_GB\n"
"localedef -i en_GB -f UTF-8 en_GB.UTF-8\n"
"localedef -i en_HK -f ISO-8859-1 en_HK\n"
"localedef -i en_PH -f ISO-8859-1 en_PH\n"
"localedef -i en_US -f ISO-8859-1 en_US\n"
"localedef -i en_US -f UTF-8 en_US.UTF-8\n"
"localedef -i es_ES -f ISO-8859-15 es_ES@euro\n"
"localedef -i es_MX -f ISO-8859-1 es_MX\n"
"localedef -i fa_IR -f UTF-8 fa_IR\n"
"localedef -i fr_FR -f ISO-8859-1 fr_FR\n"
"localedef -i fr_FR@euro -f ISO-8859-15 fr_FR@euro\n"
"localedef -i fr_FR -f UTF-8 fr_FR.UTF-8\n"
"localedef -i is_IS -f ISO-8859-1 is_IS\n"
"localedef -i is_IS -f UTF-8 is_IS.UTF-8\n"
"localedef -i it_IT -f ISO-8859-1 it_IT\n"
"localedef -i it_IT -f ISO-8859-15 it_IT@euro\n"
"localedef -i it_IT -f UTF-8 it_IT.UTF-8\n"
"localedef -i ja_JP -f EUC-JP ja_JP\n"
"localedef -i ja_JP -f UTF-8 ja_JP.UTF-8\n"
"localedef -i nl_NL@euro -f ISO-8859-15 nl_NL@euro\n"
"localedef -i ru_RU -f KOI8-R ru_RU.KOI8-R\n"
"localedef -i ru_RU -f UTF-8 ru_RU.UTF-8\n"
"localedef -i se_NO -f UTF-8 se_NO.UTF-8\n"
"localedef -i ta_IN -f UTF-8 ta_IN.UTF-8\n"
"localedef -i tr_TR -f UTF-8 tr_TR.UTF-8\n"
"localedef -i zh_CN -f GB18030 zh_CN.GB18030\n"
"localedef -i zh_HK -f BIG5-HKSCS zh_HK.BIG5-HKSCS\n"
"localedef -i zh_TW -f UTF-8 zh_TW.UTF-8</userinput>"
msgstr ""
"<userinput remap=\"locale-test\">localedef -i C -f UTF-8 C.UTF-8\n"
"localedef -i cs_CZ -f UTF-8 cs_CZ.UTF-8\n"
"localedef -i de_DE -f ISO-8859-1 de_DE\n"
"localedef -i de_DE@euro -f ISO-8859-15 de_DE@euro\n"
"localedef -i de_DE -f UTF-8 de_DE.UTF-8\n"
"localedef -i el_GR -f ISO-8859-7 el_GR\n"
"localedef -i en_GB -f ISO-8859-1 en_GB\n"
"localedef -i en_GB -f UTF-8 en_GB.UTF-8\n"
"localedef -i en_HK -f ISO-8859-1 en_HK\n"
"localedef -i en_PH -f ISO-8859-1 en_PH\n"
"localedef -i en_US -f ISO-8859-1 en_US\n"
"localedef -i en_US -f UTF-8 en_US.UTF-8\n"
"localedef -i es_ES -f ISO-8859-15 es_ES@euro\n"
"localedef -i es_MX -f ISO-8859-1 es_MX\n"
"localedef -i fa_IR -f UTF-8 fa_IR\n"
"localedef -i fr_FR -f ISO-8859-1 fr_FR\n"
"localedef -i fr_FR@euro -f ISO-8859-15 fr_FR@euro\n"
"localedef -i fr_FR -f UTF-8 fr_FR.UTF-8\n"
"localedef -i is_IS -f ISO-8859-1 is_IS\n"
"localedef -i is_IS -f UTF-8 is_IS.UTF-8\n"
"localedef -i it_IT -f ISO-8859-1 it_IT\n"
"localedef -i it_IT -f ISO-8859-15 it_IT@euro\n"
"localedef -i it_IT -f UTF-8 it_IT.UTF-8\n"
"localedef -i ja_JP -f EUC-JP ja_JP\n"
"localedef -i ja_JP -f UTF-8 ja_JP.UTF-8\n"
"localedef -i nl_NL@euro -f ISO-8859-15 nl_NL@euro\n"
"localedef -i ru_RU -f KOI8-R ru_RU.KOI8-R\n"
"localedef -i ru_RU -f UTF-8 ru_RU.UTF-8\n"
"localedef -i se_NO -f UTF-8 se_NO.UTF-8\n"
"localedef -i ta_IN -f UTF-8 ta_IN.UTF-8\n"
