#. type: Attribute 'xreflabel' of: <chapter>
#: en/chapter09/chapter09.xml:8
msgid "Chapter&nbsp;9"
msgstr "제9장"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><title>
#: en/chapter09/chapter09.xml:12
msgid "System Configuration"
msgstr "시스템 설정"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><title>
#: en/chapter09/clock.xml:11 en/chapter09/usage.xml:261
msgid "Configuring the System Clock"
msgstr "시스템 clock 설정"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><indexterm><primary>
#: en/chapter09/clock.xml:14
msgid "clock"
msgstr "clock"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/chapter09/clock.xml:17
msgid ""
"This section discusses how to configure the <command>systemd-timedated</"
"command> system service, which configures the system clock and timezone."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/chapter09/clock.xml:21
msgid ""
"If you cannot remember whether or not the hardware clock is set to UTC, find "
"out by running the <userinput>hwclock --localtime --show</userinput> "
"command. This will display what the current time is according to the "
"hardware clock. If this time matches whatever your watch says, then the "
"hardware clock is set to local time. If the output from <command>hwclock</"
"command> is not local time, chances are it is set to UTC time. Verify this "
"by adding or subtracting the proper amount of hours for the timezone to the "
"time shown by <command>hwclock</command>. For example, if you are currently "
"in the MST timezone, which is also known as GMT -0700, add seven hours to "
"the local time."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/chapter09/clock.xml:32
msgid ""
"<command>systemd-timedated</command> reads <filename>/etc/adjtime</"
"filename>, and depending on the contents of the file, sets the clock to "
"either UTC or local time."
msgstr ""
"<command>systemd-timedated</command> reads <filename>/etc/adjtime</"
"filename>, and depending on the contents of the file, sets the clock to "
"either UTC or local time."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/chapter09/clock.xml:36
msgid ""
"Create the <filename>/etc/adjtime</filename> file with the following "
"contents if your hardware clock is set to local time:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><screen>
#: en/chapter09/clock.xml:39
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<userinput>cat &gt; /etc/adjtime &lt;&lt; \"EOF\"\n"
"<literal>0.0 0 0.0\n"
"0\n"
"LOCAL</literal>\n"
"EOF</userinput>"
msgstr ""
"<userinput>cat &gt; /etc/adjtime &lt;&lt; \"EOF\"\n"
"<literal>0.0 0 0.0\n"
"0\n"
"LOCAL</literal>\n"
"EOF</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/chapter09/clock.xml:45
msgid ""
"If <filename>/etc/adjtime</filename> isn't present at first boot, "
"<command>systemd-timedated</command> will assume that hardware clock is set "
"to UTC and adjust the file according to that."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/chapter09/clock.xml:49
msgid ""
"You can also use the <command>timedatectl</command> utility to tell "
"<command>systemd-timedated</command> if your hardware clock is set to UTC or "
"local time:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><screen>
#: en/chapter09/clock.xml:53
#, no-wrap
msgid "<userinput>timedatectl set-local-rtc 1</userinput>"
msgstr "<userinput>timedatectl set-local-rtc 1</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/chapter09/clock.xml:55
msgid ""
"<command>timedatectl</command> can also be used to change system time and "
"time zone."
msgstr ""
"<command>timedatectl</command> can also be used to change system time and "
"time zone."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/chapter09/clock.xml:58
msgid "To change your current system time, issue:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><screen>
#: en/chapter09/clock.xml:60
#, no-wrap
msgid "<userinput>timedatectl set-time YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS</userinput>"
msgstr "<userinput>timedatectl set-time YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/chapter09/clock.xml:62
msgid "The hardware clock will also be updated accordingly."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/chapter09/clock.xml:64
msgid "To change your current time zone, issue:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><screen>
#: en/chapter09/clock.xml:66
#, no-wrap
msgid "<userinput>timedatectl set-timezone TIMEZONE</userinput>"
msgstr "<userinput>timedatectl set-timezone TIMEZONE</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/chapter09/clock.xml:68
msgid "You can get a list of available time zones by running:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><screen>
#: en/chapter09/clock.xml:70
#, no-wrap
msgid "<userinput>timedatectl list-timezones</userinput>"
msgstr "<userinput>timedatectl list-timezones</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><note><para>
#: en/chapter09/clock.xml:72
msgid ""
"Please note that the <command>timedatectl</command> command doesn't work in "
"the chroot environment.  It can only be used after the LFS system is booted "
"with systemd."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><title>
#: en/chapter09/clock.xml:77
msgid "Network Time Synchronization"
msgstr "Network Time Synchronization"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/chapter09/clock.xml:79
msgid ""
"Starting with version 213, systemd ships a daemon called <command>systemd-"
"timesyncd</command> which can be used to synchronize the system time with "
"remote NTP servers."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/chapter09/clock.xml:83
msgid ""
"The daemon is not intended as a replacement for the well established NTP "
"daemon, but as a client only implementation of the SNTP protocol which can "
"be used for less advanced tasks and on resource limited systems."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/chapter09/clock.xml:88
msgid ""
"Starting with systemd version 216, the <command>systemd-timesyncd</command> "
"daemon is enabled by default. If you want to disable it, issue the following "
"command:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><screen>
#: en/chapter09/clock.xml:93
#, no-wrap
msgid "<userinput>systemctl disable systemd-timesyncd</userinput>"
msgstr "<userinput>systemctl disable systemd-timesyncd</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/chapter09/clock.xml:95
msgid ""
"The <filename>/etc/systemd/timesyncd.conf</filename> file can be used to "
"change the NTP servers that <command>systemd-timesyncd</command> "
"synchronizes with."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/chapter09/clock.xml:99
msgid ""
"Please note that when system clock is set to Local Time, <command>systemd-"
"timesyncd</command> won't update hardware clock."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><title>
#: en/chapter09/consoled.xml:11 en/chapter09/usage.xml:323
msgid "Configuring the Linux Console"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/chapter09/consoled.xml:18
msgid ""
"This section discusses how to configure the <command>systemd-vconsole-setup</"
"command> system service, which configures the virtual console font and "
"console keymap."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/chapter09/consoled.xml:22
msgid ""
"The <command>systemd-vconsole-setup</command> service reads the <filename>/"
"etc/vconsole.conf</filename> file for configuration information. Decide "
"which keymap and screen font will be used. Various language-specific HOWTOs "
"can also help with this, see <ulink url=\"https://tldp.org/HOWTO/HOWTO-INDEX/"
"other-lang.html\"/>.  Examine the output of <command>localectl list-keymaps</"
"command> for a list of valid console keymaps. Look in the <filename "
"class=\"directory\">/usr/share/consolefonts</filename> directory for valid "
"screen fonts."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/chapter09/consoled.xml:32
msgid ""
"The <filename>/etc/vconsole.conf</filename> file should contain lines of the "
"form: <envar>VARIABLE=value</envar>. The following variables are recognized:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/chapter09/consoled.xml:38 en/chapter09/usage.xml:364
msgid "KEYMAP"
msgstr "KEYMAP"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/chapter09/consoled.xml:40
msgid ""
"This variable specifies the key mapping table for the keyboard. If unset, it "
"defaults to <literal>us</literal>."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/chapter09/consoled.xml:46
msgid "KEYMAP_TOGGLE"
msgstr "KEYMAP_TOGGLE"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/chapter09/consoled.xml:48
msgid ""
"This variable can be used to configure a second toggle keymap and is unset "
"by default."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/chapter09/consoled.xml:54 en/chapter09/usage.xml:392
msgid "FONT"
msgstr "FONT"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/chapter09/consoled.xml:56
msgid "This variable specifies the font used by the virtual console."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/chapter09/consoled.xml:62
msgid "FONT_MAP"
msgstr "FONT_MAP"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/chapter09/consoled.xml:64
msgid "This variable specifies the console map to be used."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/chapter09/consoled.xml:69
msgid "FONT_UNIMAP"
msgstr "FONT_UNIMAP"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/chapter09/consoled.xml:71
msgid "This variable specifies the Unicode font map."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/chapter09/consoled.xml:77
msgid ""
"We'll use <literal>C.UTF-8</literal> as the locale for interactive sessions "
"in the Linux console in <xref role='.' linkend='ch-config-locale'/> The "
"console fonts shipped by the <application>Kbd</application> package "
"containing the glyphs for all characters from the program messages in the "
"<literal>C.UTF-8</literal> locale are <filename>LatArCyrHeb*.psfu.gz</"
"filename>, <filename>LatGrkCyr*.psfu.gz</filename>, <filename>Lat2-"
"Terminus16.psfu.gz</filename>, and <filename>pancyrillic.f16.psfu.gz</"
"filename> in <filename class='directory'>/usr/share/consolefonts</filename> "
"(the other shipped console fonts lack glyphs of some characters like the "
"Unicode left/right quotation marks and the Unicode English dash). So set one "
"of them, for example <filename>Lat2-Terminus16.psfu.gz</filename> as the "
"default console font:"
msgstr ""

#.  We are using "nodump" for general settings, but not examples.  This
#.        is ironic, but needed for the compatibility with jhalfs!  
#. type: Content of: <sect1><screen>
#: en/chapter09/consoled.xml:94
#, no-wrap
msgid "<userinput>echo <literal>FONT=Lat2-Terminus16</literal> &gt; /etc/vconsole.conf</userinput>"
msgstr "<userinput>echo <literal>FONT=Lat2-Terminus16</literal> &gt; /etc/vconsole.conf</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/chapter09/consoled.xml:96
msgid "An example for a German keyboard and console is given below:"
msgstr ""

#.  This is what is used by jhalfs for creating the vconsole.conf file.
#.      Whenever you want to change the following, please inform the jhalfs
#.      maintainer(s). 
#. type: Content of: <sect1><screen>
#: en/chapter09/consoled.xml:100
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<userinput>cat &gt; /etc/vconsole.conf &lt;&lt; \"EOF\"\n"
"<literal>KEYMAP=de-latin1\n"
"FONT=Lat2-Terminus16</literal>\n"
"EOF</userinput>"
msgstr ""
"<userinput>cat &gt; /etc/vconsole.conf &lt;&lt; \"EOF\"\n"
"<literal>KEYMAP=de-latin1\n"
"FONT=Lat2-Terminus16</literal>\n"
"EOF</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/chapter09/consoled.xml:105
msgid ""
"You can change KEYMAP value at runtime by using the <command>localectl</"
"command> utility:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><screen>
#: en/chapter09/consoled.xml:108
#, no-wrap
msgid "<userinput>localectl set-keymap MAP</userinput>"
msgstr "<userinput>localectl set-keymap MAP</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><note><para>
#: en/chapter09/consoled.xml:110 en/chapter09/locale.xml:192
msgid ""
"Please note that the <command>localectl</command> command doesn't work in "
"the chroot environment.  It can only be used after the LFS system is booted "
"with systemd."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/chapter09/consoled.xml:114
msgid ""
"You can also use <command>localectl</command> utility with the corresponding "
"parameters to change X11 keyboard layout, model, variant and options:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><screen>
#: en/chapter09/consoled.xml:118
#, no-wrap
msgid "<userinput>localectl set-x11-keymap LAYOUT [MODEL] [VARIANT] [OPTIONS]</userinput>"
msgstr "<userinput>localectl set-x11-keymap LAYOUT [MODEL] [VARIANT] [OPTIONS]</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/chapter09/consoled.xml:120
msgid ""
"To list possible values for <command>localectl set-x11-keymap</command> "
"parameters, run <command>localectl</command> with parameters listed below:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/chapter09/consoled.xml:127
msgid "list-x11-keymap-models"
msgstr "list-x11-keymap-models"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/chapter09/consoled.xml:129
msgid "Shows known X11 keyboard mapping models."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/chapter09/consoled.xml:134
msgid "list-x11-keymap-layouts"
msgstr "list-x11-keymap-layouts"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/chapter09/consoled.xml:136
msgid "Shows known X11 keyboard mapping layouts."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/chapter09/consoled.xml:141
msgid "list-x11-keymap-variants"
msgstr "list-x11-keymap-variants"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/chapter09/consoled.xml:143
msgid "Shows known X11 keyboard mapping variants."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/chapter09/consoled.xml:148
msgid "list-x11-keymap-options"
msgstr "list-x11-keymap-options"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/chapter09/consoled.xml:150
msgid "Shows known X11 keyboard mapping options."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><note><para>
#: en/chapter09/consoled.xml:156
msgid ""
"Using any of the parameters listed above requires the XKeyboard-Config "
"package from BLFS."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><title>
#: en/chapter09/etcshells.xml:8 en/chapter09/etcshells.xml:11
msgid "Creating the /etc/shells File"
msgstr "/etc/shells 파일 생성"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><indexterm><primary>
#: en/chapter09/etcshells.xml:14
msgid "/etc/shells"
msgstr "/etc/shells"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/chapter09/etcshells.xml:17
msgid ""
"The <filename>shells</filename> file contains a list of login shells on the "
"system. Applications use this file to determine whether a shell is valid. "
"For each shell a single line should be present, consisting of the shell's "
"path relative to the root of the directory structure (/)."
msgstr ""
"<filename>shells</filename> 파일은 시스템에 있는 로그인 셸 목록을 담고 있습니"
"다. 애플리케이션은 이 파일을 써서 특정 셸이 유효한지 확인합니다. 각 셸에 대"
"해 디렉터리 구조의 루트(/)를 기준으로 한 셸의 경로를 한 줄에 하나씩 기록해야 "
"합니다."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/chapter09/etcshells.xml:23
msgid ""
"For example, this file is consulted by <command>chsh</command> to determine "
"whether an unprivileged user may change the login shell for her own account. "
"If the command name is not listed, the user will be denied the ability to "
"change shells."
msgstr ""
"예를 들어, 일반 사용자가 자신의 계정에 대한 로그인 셸을 변경할 수 있는지 결정"
"할 때 <command>chsh</command> 명령어가 이 파일을 참조합니다. 만약 해당 셸 이"
"름이 목록에 없다면, 사용자 셸 변경 권한은 거부됩니다."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/chapter09/etcshells.xml:28
msgid ""
"It is a requirement for applications such as <application>GDM</application> "
"which does not populate the face browser if it can't find <filename>/etc/"
"shells</filename>, or FTP daemons which traditionally disallow access to "
"users with shells not included in this file."
msgstr ""
"이 파일은 <filename>/etc/shells</filename>를 찾지 못하면 face browser(사용자 "
"목록)를 채우지 않는 <application>GDM</application>과 같은 애플리케이션이나, "
"전통적으로 이 파일에 포함되지 않은 셸을 사용하는 사용자의 접근을 거부하는 "
"FTP 데몬 등에게 필수적인 요구 사항입니다."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><screen>
#: en/chapter09/etcshells.xml:34
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<userinput>cat &gt; /etc/shells &lt;&lt; \"EOF\"\n"
"<literal># Begin /etc/shells\n"
"\n"
"/bin/sh\n"
"/bin/bash\n"
"\n"
"# End /etc/shells</literal>\n"
"EOF</userinput>"
msgstr ""
"<userinput>cat &gt; /etc/shells &lt;&lt; \"EOF\"\n"
"<literal># Begin /etc/shells\n"
"\n"
"/bin/sh\n"
"/bin/bash\n"
"\n"
"# End /etc/shells</literal>\n"
"EOF</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><title>
#: en/chapter09/inputrc.xml:11
msgid "Creating the /etc/inputrc File"
msgstr "/etc/inputrc 파일 생성"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/chapter09/inputrc.xml:14 en/chapter11/reboot.xml:93
msgid "/etc/inputrc"
msgstr "/etc/inputrc"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/chapter09/inputrc.xml:17
msgid ""
"The <filename>inputrc</filename> file is the configuration file for the "
"readline library, which provides editing capabilities while the user is "
"entering a line from the terminal. It works by translating keyboard inputs "
"into specific actions.  Readline is used by bash and most other shells as "
"well as many other applications."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/chapter09/inputrc.xml:23
msgid ""
"Most people do not need user-specific functionality so the command below "
"creates a global <filename>/etc/inputrc</filename> used by everyone who logs "
"in. If you later decide you need to override the defaults on a per user "
"basis, you can create a <filename>.inputrc</filename> file in the user's "
"home directory with the modified mappings."
msgstr ""
"대부분의 사람에게는 사용자별로 특화된 기능이 필요하지 않으므로, 아래의 명령어"
"는 로그인하는 모든 이가 사용하는 전역 <filename>/etc/inputrc</filename> 파일"
"을 생성합니다. 나중에 사용자별로 기본값을 재정의해야겠다고 결정한다면, 수정"
"된 매핑 내용을 담은 <filename>.inputrc</filename> 파일을 해당 사용자의 홈 디"
"렉터리에 생성하면 됩니다."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/chapter09/inputrc.xml:29
msgid ""
"For more information on how to edit the <filename>inputrc</filename> file, "
"see <command>info bash</command> under the <emphasis>Readline Init File</"
"emphasis> section. <command>info readline</command> is also a good source of "
"information."
msgstr ""
"<filename>inputrc</filename> 파일을 수정하는 방법에 관한 더 자세한 정보는 "
"<command>info bash</command>의 Readline Init File 섹션을 참조하십시오. "
"<command>info readline</command> 역시 훌륭한 정보원입니다."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/chapter09/inputrc.xml:34
msgid ""
"Below is a generic global <filename>inputrc</filename> along with comments "
"to explain what the various options do. Note that comments cannot be on the "
"same line as commands. Create the file using the following command:"
msgstr ""
"아래는 다양한 옵션이 무엇을 하는지 설명하는 주석이 포함된 일반적인 전역 "
"<filename>inputrc</filename> 파일입니다. 주석은 명령어와 같은 줄에 있을 수 없"
"다는 점에 유의하십시오. 다음 명령어를 사용하여 파일을 생성하십시오:"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><screen>
#: en/chapter09/inputrc.xml:38
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<userinput>cat &gt; /etc/inputrc &lt;&lt; \"EOF\"\n"
"<literal># Begin /etc/inputrc\n"
"# Modified by Chris Lynn &lt;roryo@roryo.dynup.net&gt;\n"
"\n"
"# Allow the command prompt to wrap to the next line\n"
"set horizontal-scroll-mode Off\n"
"\n"
"# Enable 8-bit input\n"
"set meta-flag On\n"
"set input-meta On\n"
"\n"
"# Turns off 8th bit stripping\n"
"set convert-meta Off\n"
"\n"
"# Keep the 8th bit for display\n"
"set output-meta On\n"
"\n"
"# none, visible or audible\n"
"set bell-style none\n"
"\n"
"# All of the following map the escape sequence of the value\n"
"# contained in the 1st argument to the readline specific functions\n"
"\"\\eOd\": backward-word\n"
"\"\\eOc\": forward-word\n"
"\n"
"# for linux console\n"
"\"\\e[1~\": beginning-of-line\n"
"\"\\e[4~\": end-of-line\n"
"\"\\e[5~\": beginning-of-history\n"
"\"\\e[6~\": end-of-history\n"
"\"\\e[3~\": delete-char\n"
"\"\\e[2~\": quoted-insert\n"
"\n"
"# for xterm\n"
"\"\\eOH\": beginning-of-line\n"
"\"\\eOF\": end-of-line\n"
"\n"
"# for Konsole\n"
"\"\\e[H\": beginning-of-line\n"
"\"\\e[F\": end-of-line\n"
"\n"
"# End /etc/inputrc</literal>\n"
"EOF</userinput>"
msgstr ""
"<userinput>cat &gt; /etc/inputrc &lt;&lt; \"EOF\"\n"
"<literal># Begin /etc/inputrc\n"
"# Modified by Chris Lynn &lt;roryo@roryo.dynup.net&gt;\n"
"\n"
"# Allow the command prompt to wrap to the next line\n"
"set horizontal-scroll-mode Off\n"
"\n"
"# Enable 8-bit input\n"
"set meta-flag On\n"
"set input-meta On\n"
"\n"
"# Turns off 8th bit stripping\n"
"set convert-meta Off\n"
"\n"
"# Keep the 8th bit for display\n"
"set output-meta On\n"
"\n"
"# none, visible or audible\n"
"set bell-style none\n"
"\n"
"# All of the following map the escape sequence of the value\n"
"# contained in the 1st argument to the readline specific functions\n"
"\"\\eOd\": backward-word\n"
"\"\\eOc\": forward-word\n"
"\n"
"# for linux console\n"
"\"\\e[1~\": beginning-of-line\n"
"\"\\e[4~\": end-of-line\n"
"\"\\e[5~\": beginning-of-history\n"
"\"\\e[6~\": end-of-history\n"
"\"\\e[3~\": delete-char\n"
"\"\\e[2~\": quoted-insert\n"
"\n"
"# for xterm\n"
"\"\\eOH\": beginning-of-line\n"
"\"\\eOF\": end-of-line\n"
"\n"
"# for Konsole\n"
"\"\\e[H\": beginning-of-line\n"
"\"\\e[F\": end-of-line\n"
"\n"
"# End /etc/inputrc</literal>\n"
"EOF</userinput>"

