#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/chapter10/kernel.xml:267
msgid "<parameter>Automount devtmpfs at /dev</parameter>"
msgstr "<parameter>Automount devtmpfs at /dev</parameter>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/chapter10/kernel.xml:269
msgid ""
"This will mount the kernel view of the devices on /dev upon switching to "
"root filesystem just before starting init."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/chapter10/kernel.xml:277
msgid ""
"<parameter> Display a user-friendly message when a kernel panic occurs </"
"parameter>"
msgstr ""
"<parameter> Display a user-friendly message when a kernel panic occurs </"
"parameter>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/chapter10/kernel.xml:282
msgid ""
"This will make the kernel correctly display the message in case a kernel "
"panic happens and a running DRM driver supports to do so.  Without this, it "
"would be more difficult to diagnose a panic: if no DRM driver is running, "
"we'd be on the VGA console which can only hold 24 lines and the relevant "
"kernel message is often flushed away; if a DRM driver is running, the "
"display is often completely messed up on panic.  As of Linux-6.12, none of "
"the dedicated drivers for mainstream GPU models really supports this, but "
"it's supported by the <quote>Simple framebuffer driver</quote> which runs on "
"the VESA (or EFI) framebuffer before the dedicated GPU driver is loaded.  If "
"the dedicated GPU driver is built as a module (instead of a part of the "
"kernel image) and no initramfs is used, this functionality will work just "
"fine before the root file system is mounted and it's already enough for "
"providing information about most LFS configuration errors causing a panic "
"(for example, an incorrect <parameter>root=</parameter> setting in <xref "
"linkend='ch-bootable-grub'/>)."
msgstr ""
"이 설정은 커널 패닉이 발생하고 실행 중인 DRM 드라이버가 이를 지원할 때, 커널"
"이 메시지를 올바르게 표시하도록 해줍니다. 이것이 없다면, 패닉 원인을 진단하기"
"가 더 어려워질 것입니다: 만약 실행중인 DRM 드라이버가 없다면 24줄만 표시할 "
"수 있는 VGA 콘솔을 사용하게 되어 중요한 커널 메시지가 화면 밖으로 밀려나기 일"
"쑤이며, DRM 드라이버가 실행 중이라면 패닉 시 화면이 엉망이 되는 경우가 많습니"
"다. Linux-6.12 기준으로 주요 GPU 모델용 전용 드라이버 중 이를 제대로 지원하"
"는 것은 없지만, 전용 GPU 드라이버가 로드되기 전 VESA(또는 EFI) 프레임버퍼에"
"서 동작하는 <quote>Simple framebuffer driver</quote>는 이를 지원합니다. 만약 "
"전용 GPU 드라이버가 (커널 이미지의 일부가 아니라) 모듈로 빌드되었고 initramfs"
"를 안 쓴다면, 이 기능은 루트 파일 시스템이 마운트되기 전까지 문제없이 작동할 "
"것입니다. 이는 잘못된 <parameter>root=</parameter> 설정(<xref linkend='ch-"
"bootable-grub'/> 참고)과 같이 패닉을 유발하는 대부분의 LFS 설정 오류에 대한 "
"정보를 제공하기에 충분합니다."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/chapter10/kernel.xml:305
msgid "<parameter> Panic screen formatter </parameter>"
msgstr "<parameter> Panic screen formatter </parameter>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/chapter10/kernel.xml:310
msgid ""
"Set this <literal>kmsg</literal> to make sure the last kernel messages lines "
"are displayed when a kernel panic happens.  The default, <literal>user</"
"literal>, would make the kernel show only a <quote>user friendly</quote> "
"panic message which is not helpful on diagnostic.  The third choice, "
"<literal>qr_code</literal>, would make the kernel to compress the last "
"kernel message lines into a QR code and display it.  The QR code can hold "
"more message lines than plain text and it can be decoded with an external "
"device (like a smart phone).  But it requires a Rust compiler that LFS does "
"not provide."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/chapter10/kernel.xml:325
msgid ""
"<parameter> Mark VGA/VBE/EFI FB as generic system framebuffer </parameter> "
"and <parameter>Simple framebuffer driver</parameter>"
msgstr ""
"<parameter> Mark VGA/VBE/EFI FB as generic system framebuffer </parameter> "
"and <parameter>Simple framebuffer driver</parameter>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/chapter10/kernel.xml:331
msgid ""
"These allow to use the VESA framebuffer (or the EFI framebuffer if booting "
"the LFS system via UEFI) as a DRM device.  The VESA framebuffer will be set "
"up by GRUB (or the EFI framebuffer will be set up by the UEFI firmware), so "
"the DRM panic handler can function before the GPU-specific DRM driver is "
"loaded."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/chapter10/kernel.xml:342
msgid ""
"<parameter> Enable legacy fbdev support for your modesetting driver </"
"parameter> and <parameter>Framebuffer Console support</parameter>"
msgstr ""
"<parameter> Enable legacy fbdev support for your modesetting driver </"
"parameter> and <parameter>Framebuffer Console support</parameter>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/chapter10/kernel.xml:348
msgid ""
"These are needed to display the Linux console on a GPU driven by a DRI "
"(Direct Rendering Infrastructure) driver.  As <option>CONFIG_DRM</option> "
"(Direct Rendering Manager) is enabled, we should enable these two options as "
"well or we'll see a blank screen once the DRI driver is loaded."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/chapter10/kernel.xml:357
msgid "<parameter>Support x2apic</parameter>"
msgstr "<parameter>Support x2apic</parameter>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/chapter10/kernel.xml:359
msgid ""
"Support running the interrupt controller of 64-bit x86 processors in x2APIC "
"mode.  x2APIC may be enabled by firmware on 64-bit x86 systems, and a kernel "
"without this option enabled will panic on boot if x2APIC is enabled by "
"firmware.  This option has no effect, but also does no harm if x2APIC is "
"disabled by the firmware."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/chapter10/kernel.xml:370
msgid ""
"Alternatively, <command>make oldconfig</command> may be more appropriate in "
"some situations. See the <filename>README</filename> file for more "
"information."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/chapter10/kernel.xml:374
msgid ""
"If desired, skip kernel configuration by copying the kernel config file, "
"<filename>.config</filename>, from the host system (assuming it is "
"available) to the unpacked <filename class=\"directory\">linux-&linux-"
"version;</filename> directory. However, we do not recommend this option. It "
"is often better to explore all the configuration menus and create the kernel "
"configuration from scratch."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/chapter10/kernel.xml:382
msgid "Compile the kernel image and modules:"
msgstr "커널 이미지 및 모듈 컴파일:"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/chapter10/kernel.xml:386
msgid ""
"If using kernel modules, module configuration in <filename "
"class=\"directory\">/etc/modprobe.d</filename> may be required.  Information "
"pertaining to modules and kernel configuration is located in <xref "
"linkend=\"ch-config-udev\"/> and in the kernel documentation in the "
"<filename class=\"directory\">linux-&linux-version;/Documentation</filename> "
"directory.  Also, <ulink role='man' url='&man;modprobe.d.5'>modprobe.d(5)</"
"ulink> may be of interest."
msgstr ""
"커널 모듈을 사용하면, <filename class=\"directory\">/etc/modprobe.d</"
"filename> 디렉터리에서 모듈 설정이 필요할 수 있습니다. 모듈 및 커널 설정에 관"
"한 정보는 <xref linkend=\"ch-config-udev\"/> 및 커널 소스의 <filename "
"class=\"directory\">linux-&linux-version;/Documentation</filename> 디렉터리"
"에 있는 커널 문서에 들어 있습니다. 또한, <ulink role='man' "
"url='&man;modprobe.d.5'>modprobe.d(5)</ulink> 역시 참고할 만합니다."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/chapter10/kernel.xml:395
msgid ""
"Unless module support has been disabled in the kernel configuration, install "
"the modules with:"
msgstr ""
"커널 설정에서 모듈 지원을 비활성화하지 않았다면, 다음 명령으로 모듈을 설치:"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><screen>
#: en/chapter10/kernel.xml:398
#, no-wrap
msgid "<userinput remap=\"install\">make modules_install</userinput>"
msgstr "<userinput remap=\"install\">make modules_install</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/chapter10/kernel.xml:400
msgid ""
"After kernel compilation is complete, additional steps are required to "
"complete the installation. Some files need to be copied to the <filename "
"class=\"directory\">/boot</filename> directory."
msgstr ""
"커널 컴파일 완료 후, 설치를 마무리하기 위해 추가 단계가 필요합니다. 일부 파일"
"을 <filename class=\"directory\">/boot</filename> 디렉터리로 복사해야 합니다."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><caution><para>
#: en/chapter10/kernel.xml:405
msgid ""
"If you've decided to use a separate &boot-dir; partition for the LFS system "
"(maybe sharing a &boot-dir; partition with the host distro), the files "
"copied below should go there. The easiest way to do that is to create the "
"entry for &boot-dir; in &fstab; first (read the previous section for "
"details), then issue the following command as the &root; user in the "
"<emphasis>chroot environment</emphasis>:"
msgstr ""
"만약 별도의 &boot-dir; 파티션을 LFS 시스템을 위해 사용하기로 결정했다면(아마"
"도 호스트 배포판과 &boot-dir; 파티션을 공유하는 경우일 것입니다), 아래에서 복"
"사하는 파일들은 그곳에 저장되어야 합니다. 이를 위한 가장 쉬운 방법은 먼저 "
"&fstab; 에 &boot-dir; 에 대한 항목을 만드는 것이며(자세한 내용은 이전 섹션 참"
"고), 그 후 <emphasis>chroot 환경</emphasis> 에서 &root; 사용자로 다음 명령을 "
"실행:"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><caution><screen>
#: en/chapter10/kernel.xml:413
#, no-wrap
msgid "<userinput>mount /boot</userinput>"
msgstr "<userinput>mount /boot</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><caution><para>
#: en/chapter10/kernel.xml:415
msgid ""
"The path to the device node is omitted in the command because "
"<command>mount</command> can read it from &fstab;."
msgstr ""
"장치 노드에 대한 경로는 명령에서 생략했는데 왜냐면<command>mount</command> "
"는 &fstab; 에서 경로를 읽어올 수 있기 때문입니다."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/chapter10/kernel.xml:419
msgid ""
"The path to the kernel image may vary depending on the platform being used. "
"The filename below can be changed to suit your taste, but the stem of the "
"filename should be <emphasis>vmlinuz</emphasis> to be compatible with the "
"automatic setup of the boot process described in the next section.  The "
"following command assumes an x86 architecture:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><screen>
#: en/chapter10/kernel.xml:425
#, no-wrap
msgid "<userinput remap=\"install\">cp -iv arch/x86/boot/bzImage /boot/vmlinuz-&linux-version;-lfs-&version;</userinput>"
msgstr "<userinput remap=\"install\">cp -iv arch/x86/boot/bzImage /boot/vmlinuz-&linux-version;-lfs-&version;</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/chapter10/kernel.xml:427
msgid ""
"<filename>System.map</filename> is a symbol file for the kernel.  It maps "
"the function entry points of every function in the kernel API, as well as "
"the addresses of the kernel data structures for the running kernel.  It is "
"used as a resource when investigating kernel problems.  Issue the following "
"command to install the map file:"
msgstr ""
"<filename>System.map</filename> is a symbol file for the kernel.  It maps "
"the function entry points of every function in the kernel API, as well as "
"the addresses of the kernel data structures for the running kernel.  It is "
"used as a resource when investigating kernel problems.  Issue the following "
"command to install the map file:"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><screen>
#: en/chapter10/kernel.xml:433
#, no-wrap
msgid "<userinput remap=\"install\">cp -iv System.map /boot/System.map-&linux-version;</userinput>"
msgstr "<userinput remap=\"install\">cp -iv System.map /boot/System.map-&linux-version;</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/chapter10/kernel.xml:435
msgid ""
"The kernel configuration file <filename>.config</filename> produced by the "
"<command>make menuconfig</command> step above contains all the configuration "
"selections for the kernel that was just compiled. It is a good idea to keep "
"this file for future reference:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><screen>
#: en/chapter10/kernel.xml:441
#, no-wrap
msgid "<userinput remap=\"install\">cp -iv .config /boot/config-&linux-version;</userinput>"
msgstr "<userinput remap=\"install\">cp -iv .config /boot/config-&linux-version;</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/chapter10/kernel.xml:443
msgid "Install the documentation for the Linux kernel:"
msgstr "리눅스 커널용 문서 설치하기:"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><screen>
#: en/chapter10/kernel.xml:445
#, no-wrap
msgid "<userinput remap=\"install\">cp -r Documentation -T /usr/share/doc/linux-&linux-version;</userinput>"
msgstr "<userinput remap=\"install\">cp -r Documentation -T /usr/share/doc/linux-&linux-version;</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/chapter10/kernel.xml:447
msgid ""
"It is important to note that the files in the kernel source directory are "
"not owned by <emphasis>root</emphasis>. Whenever a package is unpacked as "
"user <emphasis>root</emphasis> (like we did inside chroot), the files have "
"the user and group IDs of whatever they were on the packager's computer. "
"This is usually not a problem for any other package to be installed because "
"the source tree is removed after the installation. However, the Linux source "
"tree is often retained for a long time.  Because of this, there is a chance "
"that whatever user ID the packager used will be assigned to somebody on the "
"machine. That person would then have write access to the kernel source."
msgstr ""
"커널 소스 디렉터리에 있는 파일들의 소유권이 <emphasis>root</emphasis> 아니라"
"는 점에 유의하는 것이 중요합니다. 패키지가 <emphasis>root</emphasis> 사용자"
"로 압축 해제될 때마다(우리가 chroot 내부에서 했던 것처럼), 파일들은 패키지 제"
"작자의 컴퓨터에 설정되어 있던 사용자 및 그룹 ID를 갖게 됩니다. 다른 패키지들"
"의 경우 설치 후에 소스 트리를 삭제하므로 대개 문제가 되지 않습니다. 하지만 리"
"눅스 소스 트리는 종종 오랫동안 유지되곤 합니다. 이 때문에 패키지 제작자가 사"
"용했던 사용자 ID가 우리 시스템의 누군가에게 할당될 가능성이 있으며, 그렇게 되"
"면 그 사람이 커널 소스에 대한 쓰기 권한을 가지게 될 수도 있습니다."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><note><para>
#: en/chapter10/kernel.xml:460
msgid ""
"In many cases, the configuration of the kernel will need to be updated for "
"packages that will be installed later in BLFS.  Unlike other packages, it is "
"not necessary to remove the kernel source tree after the newly built kernel "
"is installed."
msgstr ""
"많은 경우, 나중에 커널 설정의 업데이트가 BLFS에서 설치할 패키지를 위해 필요"
"할 것입니다. 다른 패키지와 달리, 새로 빌드된 커널이 설치된 후에도 커널 소스 "
"트리를 제거할 필요가 없습니다."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><note><para>
#: en/chapter10/kernel.xml:465
msgid ""
"If the kernel source tree is going to be retained, run <command>chown -R "
"0:0</command> on the <filename class=\"directory\">linux-&linux-version;</"
"filename> directory to ensure all files are owned by user <emphasis>root</"
"emphasis>."
msgstr ""
"만약 커널 소스 트리를 유지할 계획이라면, <filename class=\"directory\">linux-"
"&linux-version;</filename> 디렉터리에 <command>chown -R 0:0</command> 실행하"
"여 모든 파일의 소유권이 <emphasis>root</emphasis> 사용자에게 있도록 하십시오."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><note><para>
#: en/chapter10/kernel.xml:470
msgid ""
"If you are updating the configuration and rebuilding the kernel from a "
"retained kernel source tree, normally you should <emphasis role='bold'>not</"
"emphasis> run the <command>make mrproper</command> command.  The command "
"would purge the <filename>.config</filename> file and all the <filename "
"class='extension'>.o</filename> files from the previous build.  Despite it's "
"easy to restore <filename>.config</filename> from the copy in <filename "
"class='directory'>/boot</filename>, purging all the <filename "
"class='extension'>.o</filename> files is still a waste: for a simple "
"configuration change, often only a few <filename class='extension'>.o</"
"filename> files need to be (re)built and the kernel build system will "
"correctly skip other <filename class='extension'>.o</filename> files if they "
"are not purged."
msgstr ""
"만약 유지해 온 커널 소스 트리에서 설정을 업데이트하고 커널을 다시 빌드하는 중"
"이라면, 대개 <command>make mrproper</command> 명령을 실행하면 <emphasis "
"role='bold'>안 됩니다</emphasis>. 왜냐하면 이 명령은 <filename>.config</"
"filename> 파일과 이전 빌드에서 생성된 모든 <filename class='extension'>.o</"
"filename> 파일들을 삭제하기 때문입니다. <filename class='directory'>/boot</"
"filename> 디렉터리에 복사해 둔 설정값으로 <filename>.config</filename>를 복구"
"하는 것은 쉽지만, 모든 <filename class='extension'>.o</filename> 파일들을 삭"
"제하는 것은 여전히 낭비입니다. 단순한 설정 변경의 경우 대개 몇 개의 "
"<filename class='extension'>.o</filename> 파일만 다시 빌드하면 되는데, 커널 "
"빌드 시스템은 파일들이 삭제되지 않았다면 나머지 <filename "
"class='extension'>.o</filename> 파일들을 올바르게 건너뛰기 때문입니다."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><note><para>
#: en/chapter10/kernel.xml:485
msgid ""
"On the other hand, if you've upgraded GCC, you should run <command>make "
"clean</command> to purge all the <filename class='extension'>.o</filename> "
"files from the previous build, or the new build may fail."
msgstr ""
"반면에, 만약 GCC를 업그레이드했다면 <command>make clean</command> 실행하여 이"
"전 빌드의 모든 <filename class='extension'>.o</filename> 파일들을 삭제해야 하"
"는데, 안 그러면 새로운 빌드가 실패할 수 있기 때문입니다."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><warning><para>
#: en/chapter10/kernel.xml:492
msgid ""
"Some kernel documentation recommends creating a symlink from <filename "
"class=\"symlink\">/usr/src/linux</filename> pointing to the kernel source "
"directory.  This is specific to kernels prior to the 2.6 series and "
"<emphasis>must not</emphasis> be created on an LFS system as it can cause "
"problems for packages you may wish to build once your base LFS system is "
"complete."
msgstr ""
"일부 커널 문서에서는 <filename class=\"symlink\">/usr/src/linux</filename>에"
"서 커널 소스 디렉터리를 가리키는 심볼릭 링크를 만들 것을 권장합니다. 이는 "
"2.6 시리즈 이전의 커널에만 해당되는 사항이며, LFS 시스템에서는 <emphasis>만들"
"면 안 되는데</emphasis> 왜냐면 기본 LFS 시스템이 완성된 후 여러분이 빌드하고"
"자 하는 패키지에 문제를 일으킬 수 있기 때문입니다."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><title>
#: en/chapter10/kernel.xml:503
msgid "Configuring Linux Module Load Order"
msgstr "리눅스 모듈 로드 순서 설정하기"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><indexterm><primary>
#: en/chapter10/kernel.xml:506
msgid "/etc/modprobe.d/usb.conf"
msgstr "/etc/modprobe.d/usb.conf"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/chapter10/kernel.xml:509
msgid ""
"Most of the time Linux modules are loaded automatically, but sometimes it "
"needs some specific direction.  The program that loads modules, "
"<command>modprobe</command> or <command>insmod</command>, uses <filename>/"
"etc/modprobe.d/usb.conf</filename> for this purpose.  This file needs to be "
"created so that if the USB drivers (ehci_hcd, ohci_hcd and uhci_hcd) have "
"been built as modules, they will be loaded in the correct order; ehci_hcd "
"needs to be loaded prior to ohci_hcd and uhci_hcd in order to avoid a "
"warning being output at boot time."
msgstr ""
"대부분의 경우 리눅스 모듈은 자동으로 로드되지만, 때로는 구체적인 지시가 필요"
"할 때가 있습니다. 모듈을 로드하는 프로그램 <command>modprobe</command> 또는 "
"<command>insmod</command>는 이 목적으로 <filename>/etc/modprobe.d/usb.conf</"
"filename>를 사용합니다. 이 파일은 USB 드라이버(ehci_hcd, ohci_hcd, uhci_hcd)"
"가 모듈로 빌드되었을 경우 올바른 순서로 로드되도록 생성해야 하는데, 왜냐면 부"
"팅 시 경고 메시지가 출력되는 것을 피하려면 ehci_hcd가 ohci_hcd 및 uhci_hcd보"
"다 먼저 로드되어야 하기 때문입니다."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/chapter10/kernel.xml:518
msgid ""
"Create a new file <filename>/etc/modprobe.d/usb.conf</filename> by running "
"the following:"
msgstr "새 파일 <filename>/etc/modprobe.d/usb.conf</filename> 만들려면 실행:"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><screen>
#: en/chapter10/kernel.xml:521
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<userinput>install -v -m755 -d /etc/modprobe.d\n"
"cat &gt; /etc/modprobe.d/usb.conf &lt;&lt; \"EOF\"\n"
"<literal># Begin /etc/modprobe.d/usb.conf\n"
"\n"
"install ohci_hcd /sbin/modprobe ehci_hcd ; /sbin/modprobe -i ohci_hcd ; true\n"
"install uhci_hcd /sbin/modprobe ehci_hcd ; /sbin/modprobe -i uhci_hcd ; true\n"
"\n"
"# End /etc/modprobe.d/usb.conf</literal>\n"
"EOF</userinput>"
msgstr ""
"<userinput>install -v -m755 -d /etc/modprobe.d\n"
"cat &gt; /etc/modprobe.d/usb.conf &lt;&lt; \"EOF\"\n"
"<literal># Begin /etc/modprobe.d/usb.conf\n"
"\n"
"install ohci_hcd /sbin/modprobe ehci_hcd ; /sbin/modprobe -i ohci_hcd ; true\n"
"install uhci_hcd /sbin/modprobe ehci_hcd ; /sbin/modprobe -i uhci_hcd ; true\n"
"\n"
"# End /etc/modprobe.d/usb.conf</literal>\n"
"EOF</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><title>
#: en/chapter10/kernel.xml:534
msgid "Contents of Linux"
msgstr "Linux 구성 요소"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><segmentedlist><seglistitem><seg>
#: en/chapter10/kernel.xml:541
msgid ""
"config-&linux-version;, vmlinuz-&linux-version;-lfs-&version;, and "
"System.map-&linux-version;"
msgstr ""
"config-&linux-version;, vmlinuz-&linux-version;-lfs-&version;, 및 System.map-"
"&linux-version;"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><segmentedlist><seglistitem><seg>
#: en/chapter10/kernel.xml:544
msgid "/lib/modules, /usr/share/doc/linux-&linux-version;"
msgstr "/lib/modules, /usr/share/doc/linux-&linux-version;"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/chapter10/kernel.xml:554
msgid "<filename>config-&linux-version;</filename>"
msgstr "<filename>config-&linux-version;</filename>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/chapter10/kernel.xml:556
msgid "Contains all the configuration selections for the kernel"
msgstr "커널용 설정 선택 사항을 모두 포함"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><indexterm><primary>
#: en/chapter10/kernel.xml:558
msgid "/boot/config-&linux-version;"
msgstr "/boot/config-&linux-version;"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/chapter10/kernel.xml:564
msgid "<filename>vmlinuz-&linux-version;-lfs-&version;</filename>"
msgstr "<filename>vmlinuz-&linux-version;-lfs-&version;</filename>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/chapter10/kernel.xml:566
msgid ""
"The engine of the Linux system. When turning on the computer, the kernel is "
"the first part of the operating system that gets loaded.  It detects and "
"initializes all components of the computer's hardware, then makes these "
"components available as a tree of files to the software and turns a single "
"CPU into a multitasking machine capable of running scores of programs "
"seemingly at the same time"
msgstr ""
"리눅스 시스템의 엔진. 컴퓨터를 켤 때, 커널은 운영체제에서 가장 먼저 로드되는 "
"부분입니다. 커널은 컴퓨터 하드웨어의 모든 구성 요소를 감지하고 초기화한 다"
"음, 이 요소들을 소프트웨어가 사용할 수 있도록 파일 트리 형태로 제공합니다. 또"
"한 단일 CPU를 수십 개의 프로그램을 겉보기에 동시에 실행할 수 있는 멀티태스킹 "
"머신으로 만듦"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><indexterm><primary>
#: en/chapter10/kernel.xml:573
msgid "lfskernel-&linux-version;"
msgstr "lfskernel-&linux-version;"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/chapter10/kernel.xml:579
msgid "<filename>System.map-&linux-version;</filename>"
msgstr "<filename>System.map-&linux-version;</filename>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/chapter10/kernel.xml:581
msgid ""
"A list of addresses and symbols; it maps the entry points and addresses of "
"all the functions and data structures in the kernel"
msgstr ""
"주소 및 심볼 목록. 이는 커널에 있는 모든 함수와 데이터 구조의 진입점(entry "
"point) 및 주소를 매핑"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><indexterm><primary>
#: en/chapter10/kernel.xml:585
msgid "/boot/System.map-&linux-version;"
msgstr "/boot/System.map-&linux-version;"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><title>
#: en/chapter11/afterlfs.xml:11
msgid "Getting Started After LFS"
msgstr "LFS 이후 시작하기"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><title>
#: en/chapter11/afterlfs.xml:14
msgid "Deciding what to do next"
msgstr "다음에 할 것 결정하기"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/chapter11/afterlfs.xml:17
msgid ""
"Now that LFS is complete and you have a bootable system, what do you do? The "
"next step is to decide how to use it. Generally, there are two broad "
"categories to consider: workstation or server. Indeed, these categories are "
"not mutually exclusive. The applications needed for each category can be "
"combined onto a single system, but let's look at them separately for now."
msgstr ""
"이제 LFS가 완성되어 부팅 가능한 시스템을 갖추었으니, 무엇을 해야 할까요? 다"
"음 단계는 이 시스템을 어떻게 사용할지 결정하는 것입니다. 일반적으로 워크스테"
"이션과 서버 두 가지 큰 범주를 고려해 볼 수 있습니다. 사실 이 두 범주가 서로 "
"배타적인 것은 아닙니다. 각 범주에 필요한 애플리케이션을 하나의 시스템에 통합"
"할 수도 있지만, 지금은 각각 분리해서 살펴보겠습니다."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/chapter11/afterlfs.xml:26
msgid ""
"A server is the simpler category. Generally this consists of a web server "
"such as the <ulink url=\"&blfs-book;server/apache.html\">Apache HTTP Server</"
"ulink> and a database server such as <ulink url=\"&blfs-book;server/"
"mariadb.html\">MariaDB</ulink>.  However other services are possible. The "
"operating system embedded in a single use device falls into this category."
msgstr ""
"서버는 더 단순한 범주에 속합니다. 일반적으로 이는 <ulink url=\"&blfs-"
"book;server/apache.html\">Apache HTTP 서버</ulink>와 같은 웹 서버나 <ulink "
"url=\"&blfs-book;server/mariadb.html\">MariaDB</ulink>와 같은 데이터베이스 서"
"버로 구성됩니다. 하지만 다른 서비스도 가능합니다. 단일 목적 장치(single use "
"device)에 내장된 운영 체제도 이 범주에 포함됩니다."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/chapter11/afterlfs.xml:36
msgid ""
"On the other hand, a workstation is much more complex. It generally requires "
"a graphical user environment such as <ulink url=\"&blfs-book;lxde/"
"lxde.html\">LXDE</ulink>, <ulink url=\"&blfs-book;xfce/xfce.html\">XFCE</"
"ulink>, <ulink url=\"&blfs-book;kde/kde.html\">KDE</ulink>, or <ulink "
"url=\"&blfs-book;gnome/gnome.html\">Gnome</ulink> based on a basic <ulink "
"url=\"&blfs-book;x/installing.html\">graphical environment</ulink> and "
"several graphical based applications such as the <ulink url=\"&blfs-"
"book;xsoft/firefox.html\">Firefox web browser</ulink>, <ulink url=\"&blfs-"
"book;xsoft/thunderbird.html\">Thunderbird email client</ulink>, or <ulink "
"url=\"&blfs-book;xsoft/libreoffice.html\">LibreOffice office suite</ulink>.  "
"These applications require many (several hundred depending on desired "
"capabilities) more packages of support applications and libraries."
msgstr ""
"반면, 워크스테이션은 훨씬 더 복잡합니다. 일반적으로 기초적인 <ulink "
"url=\"&blfs-book;x/installing.html\">그래픽 환경</ulink>을 기반으로 <ulink "
"url=\"&blfs-book;lxde/lxde.html\">LXDE</ulink>, <ulink url=\"&blfs-book;xfce/"
"xfce.html\">XFCE</ulink>, <ulink url=\"&blfs-book;kde/kde.html\">KDE</ulink> "
"또는 <ulink url=\"&blfs-book;gnome/gnome.html\">Gnome</ulink>과 같은 그래픽 "
"사용자 환경이 필요하며, <ulink url=\"&blfs-book;xsoft/firefox.html\">Firefox "
"웹 브라우저</ulink>, <ulink url=\"&blfs-book;xsoft/"
"thunderbird.html\">Thunderbird 이메일 클라이언트</ulink> 또는 <ulink "
"url=\"&blfs-book;xsoft/libreoffice.html\">LibreOffice 오피스 제품군</ulink>"
"과 같은 여러 그래픽 기반 애플리케이션도 필요합니다. 이러한 애플리케이션을 사"
"용하려면 원하는 기능에 따라 수백 개의 추가 지원 애플리케이션과 라이브러리 패"
"키지가 더 필요합니다."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/chapter11/afterlfs.xml:55
msgid ""
"In addition to the above, there is a set of applications for system "
"management for all kinds of systems. These applications are all in the BLFS "
"book. Not all packages are needed in every environment. For example <ulink "
"url=\"&blfs-book;basicnet/dhcpcd.html\">dhcpcd</ulink>, is not normally "
"appropriate for a server and <ulink url=\"&blfs-book;basicnet/"
"wireless_tools.html\">wireless_tools</ulink>, are normally only useful for a "
"laptop system."
msgstr ""
"앞서 언급한 것들 외에도 모든 종류의 시스템을 관리하기 위한 일련의 애플리케이"
"션이 있습니다. 이 애플리케이션은 모두 BLFS 책에 수록되어 있습니다. 모든 환경"
"에서 모든 패키지가 필요한 것은 아닙니다. 예를 들어 <ulink url=\"&blfs-"
"book;basicnet/dhcpcd.html\">dhcpcd</ulink>는 대개 서버에 적합하지 않으며, "
"<ulink url=\"&blfs-book;basicnet/wireless_tools.html\">wireless_tools</ulink>"
"는 일반적으로 노트북 시스템에서만 유용합니다."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><title>
#: en/chapter11/afterlfs.xml:67
msgid "Working in a basic LFS environment"
msgstr "기본 LFS 환경에서 작업"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/chapter11/afterlfs.xml:70
msgid ""
"When you initially boot into LFS, you have all the internal tools to build "
"additional packages. Unfortunately, the user environment is quite sparse.  "
"There are a couple of ways to improve this:"
msgstr ""
"처음 LFS로 부팅하면 추가 패키지를 빌드하는 데 필요한 내부 도구는 모두 갖춰져 "
"있습니다. 아쉽게도 사용자 환경은 매우 빈약합니다. 이를 개선할 수 있는 몇 가"
"지 방법:"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><sect3><title>
#: en/chapter11/afterlfs.xml:76
msgid "Work from the LFS host in chroot"
msgstr "chroot 환경에서 LFS 호스트를 이용한 작업"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><sect3><para>
#: en/chapter11/afterlfs.xml:79
msgid ""
"This method provides a complete graphical environment where a full featured "
"browser and copy/paste capabilities are available. This method allows using "
"applications like the host's version of wget to download package sources to "
"a location available when working in the chroot environment."
msgstr ""
"이 방법은 기능이 풍부한 브라우저와 복사/붙여넣기 기능을 사용할 수 있는 완전"
"한 그래픽 환경을 제공합니다. 또한 호스트 버전의 wget 같은 애플리케이션을 사용"
"하여, chroot 환경에서 작업할 때 접근 가능한 위치로 패키지 소스를 다운로드할 "
"수 있습니다."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><sect3><para>
#: en/chapter11/afterlfs.xml:87
msgid ""
"In order to properly build packages in chroot, you will also need to "
"remember to mount the virtual file systems if they are not already mounted. "
"One way to do this is to create a script on the <emphasis "
"role=\"bold\">HOST</emphasis> system:"
msgstr ""
"chroot 환경에서 패키지를 제대로 빌드하려면, 가상 파일 시스템이 아직 마운트 "
"안 된 경우 이를 마운트해야 한다는 점을 기억해야 합니다. 이를 위한 한 가지 방"
"법은 <emphasis role=\"bold\">HOST</emphasis> 시스템에 스크립트를 생성하는 것"
"입니다:"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><sect3><screen>
#: en/chapter11/afterlfs.xml:93
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<command>cat &gt; ~/mount-virt.sh &lt;&lt; \"EOF\"\n"
"#!/bin/bash\n"
"\n"
"function mountbind\n"
"{\n"
"   if ! mountpoint $LFS/$1 >/dev/null; then\n"
"     $SUDO mount --bind /$1 $LFS/$1\n"
"     echo $LFS/$1 mounted\n"
"   else\n"
"     echo $LFS/$1 already mounted\n"
"   fi\n"
"}\n"
"\n"
"function mounttype\n"
"{\n"
"   if ! mountpoint $LFS/$1 >/dev/null; then\n"
"     $SUDO mount -t $2 $3 $4 $5 $LFS/$1\n"
"     echo $LFS/$1 mounted\n"
"   else\n"
"     echo $LFS/$1 already mounted\n"
"   fi\n"
"}\n"
"\n"
"if [ $EUID -ne 0 ]; then\n"
"  SUDO=sudo\n"
"else\n"
"  SUDO=\"\"\n"
"fi\n"
"\n"
"if [ x$LFS == x ]; then\n"
"  echo \"LFS not set\"\n"
"  exit 1\n"
"fi\n"
"\n"
"mountbind dev\n"
"mounttype dev/pts devpts devpts -o gid=5,mode=620\n"
"mounttype proc    proc   proc\n"
"mounttype sys     sysfs  sysfs\n"
"mounttype run     tmpfs  run\n"
"if [ -h $LFS/dev/shm ]; then\n"
"  install -v -d -m 1777 $LFS$(realpath /dev/shm)\n"
"else\n"
"  mounttype dev/shm tmpfs tmpfs -o nosuid,nodev\n"
"fi \n"
"\n"
"#mountbind usr/src\n"
"#mountbind boot\n"
"#mountbind home\n"
"EOF</command>"
msgstr ""
"<command>cat &gt; ~/mount-virt.sh &lt;&lt; \"EOF\"\n"
"#!/bin/bash\n"
"\n"
"function mountbind\n"
"{\n"
"   if ! mountpoint $LFS/$1 >/dev/null; then\n"
"     $SUDO mount --bind /$1 $LFS/$1\n"
"     echo $LFS/$1 mounted\n"
"   else\n"
"     echo $LFS/$1 already mounted\n"
"   fi\n"
"}\n"
"\n"
"function mounttype\n"
"{\n"
"   if ! mountpoint $LFS/$1 >/dev/null; then\n"
"     $SUDO mount -t $2 $3 $4 $5 $LFS/$1\n"
"     echo $LFS/$1 mounted\n"
"   else\n"
"     echo $LFS/$1 already mounted\n"
"   fi\n"
"}\n"
"\n"
"if [ $EUID -ne 0 ]; then\n"
"  SUDO=sudo\n"
"else\n"
"  SUDO=\"\"\n"
"fi\n"
"\n"
"if [ x$LFS == x ]; then\n"
"  echo \"LFS not set\"\n"
"  exit 1\n"
"fi\n"
"\n"
"mountbind dev\n"
"mounttype dev/pts devpts devpts -o gid=5,mode=620\n"
"mounttype proc    proc   proc\n"
"mounttype sys     sysfs  sysfs\n"
"mounttype run     tmpfs  run\n"
"if [ -h $LFS/dev/shm ]; then\n"
"  install -v -d -m 1777 $LFS$(realpath /dev/shm)\n"
"else\n"
"  mounttype dev/shm tmpfs tmpfs -o nosuid,nodev\n"
"fi \n"
"\n"
"#mountbind usr/src\n"
"#mountbind boot\n"
"#mountbind home\n"
"EOF</command>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><sect3><para>
#: en/chapter11/afterlfs.xml:144
msgid ""
"Note that the last three commands in the script are commented out. These are "
"useful if those directories are mounted as separate partitions on the host "
"system and will be mounted when booting the completed LFS/BLFS system."
msgstr ""
"스크립트에 마지막 세 명령어가 주석 처리되어 있음에 유의하십시오. 이 명령어는 "
"해당 디렉터리가 호스트 시스템에서 별도 파티션으로 마운트되어 있으며, 완성된 "
"LFS/BLFS 시스템을 부팅할 때 마운트될 경우에 쓸 만합니다."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><sect3><para>
#: en/chapter11/afterlfs.xml:150
msgid ""
"The script can be run with <command>bash ~/mount-virt.sh</command> as either "
"a regular user (recommended) or as &root;. If run as a regular user, sudo is "
"required on the host system."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><sect3><para>
#: en/chapter11/afterlfs.xml:156
msgid ""
"Another issue pointed out by the script is where to store downloaded package "
"files. This location is arbitrary. It can be in a regular user's home "
"directory such as ~/sources or in a global location like /usr/src. Our "
"recommendation is not to mix BLFS sources and LFS sources in (from the "
"chroot environment) /sources. In any case, the packages must be accessible "
"inside the chroot environment."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><sect3><para>
#: en/chapter11/afterlfs.xml:165
msgid ""
"A last convenience feature presented here is to streamline the process of "
"entering the chroot environment. This can be done with an alias placed in a "
"user's ~/.bashrc file on the host system:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><sect3><screen>
#: en/chapter11/afterlfs.xml:170
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<command>alias lfs='sudo /usr/sbin/chroot /mnt/lfs /usr/bin/env -i HOME=/root TERM=\"$TERM\" PS1=\"\\u:\\w\\\\\\\\$ \"\n"
"PATH=/usr/bin:/usr/sbin /bin/bash --login'</command>"
msgstr ""
"<command>alias lfs='sudo /usr/sbin/chroot /mnt/lfs /usr/bin/env -i HOME=/root TERM=\"$TERM\" PS1=\"\\u:\\w\\\\\\\\$ \"\n"
"PATH=/usr/bin:/usr/sbin /bin/bash --login'</command>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><sect3><para>
#: en/chapter11/afterlfs.xml:174
msgid ""
"This alias is a little tricky because of the quoting and levels of backslash "
"characters. It must be all on a single line. The above command has been "
"split in two for presentation purposes."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><sect3><title>
#: en/chapter11/afterlfs.xml:182
msgid "Work remotely via ssh"
msgstr "ssh 통한 원격 작업"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><sect3><para>
#: en/chapter11/afterlfs.xml:185
msgid ""
"This method also provides a full graphical environment, but first requires "
"installing <ulink url=\"&blfs-book;postlfs/openssh.html\">sshd</ulink> on "
"the LFS system, usually in chroot. It also requires a second computer. This "
"method has the advantage of being simple by not requiring the complexity of "
"the chroot environment. It also uses your LFS built kernel for all "
"additional packages and still provides a complete system for installing "
"packages."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><sect3><para>
#: en/chapter11/afterlfs.xml:196
msgid ""
"You may use the <command>scp</command> command to upload the package sources "
"to be built onto the LFS system.  If you want to download the sources onto "
"the LFS system directly instead, install <ulink url=\"&blfs-book;general/"
"libtasn1.html\">libtasn1</ulink>, <ulink url=\"&blfs-book;postlfs/p11-"
"kit.html\">p11-kit</ulink>, <ulink url=\"&blfs-book;postlfs/make-"
"ca.html\">make-ca</ulink>, and <ulink url=\"&blfs-book;basicnet/"
"wget.html\">wget</ulink> in chroot (or upload their sources using "
"<command>scp</command> after booting the LFS system)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><sect3><title>
#: en/chapter11/afterlfs.xml:209
msgid "Work from the LFS command line"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><sect3><para>
#: en/chapter11/afterlfs.xml:212
msgid ""
"This method requires installing <ulink url=\"&blfs-book;general/"
"libtasn1.html\">libtasn1</ulink>, <ulink url=\"&blfs-book;postlfs/p11-"
"kit.html\">p11-kit</ulink>, <ulink url=\"&blfs-book;postlfs/make-"
"ca.html\">make-ca</ulink>, <ulink url=\"&blfs-book;basicnet/"
"wget.html\">wget</ulink>, <ulink url=\"&blfs-book;general/gpm.html\">gpm</"
"ulink>, and <ulink url=\"&blfs-book;basicnet/links.html\">links</ulink> (or "
"<ulink url=\"&blfs-book;basicnet/lynx.html\">lynx</ulink>)  in chroot and "
"then rebooting into the new LFS system. At this point the default system has "
"six virtual consoles. Switching consoles is as easy as using the <keycombo> "
"<keycap>Alt</keycap> <keycap>Fx</keycap> </keycombo> key combinations where "
"<keycap>Fx</keycap> is between <keycap>F1</keycap> and <keycap>F6</keycap>.  "
"The <keycombo> <keycap>Alt</keycap> <keycap function='left'/> </keycombo> "
"and <keycombo> <keycap>Alt</keycap> <keycap function='right'/> </keycombo> "
"combinations also will change the console."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><sect3><para>
#: en/chapter11/afterlfs.xml:243
msgid ""
"At this point you can log into two different virtual consoles and run the "
"links or lynx browser in one console and bash in the other. GPM then allows "
"copying commands from the browser with the left mouse button, switching "
"consoles, and pasting into the other console."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><sect3><note><para>
#: en/chapter11/afterlfs.xml:251
msgid ""
"As a side note, switching of virtual consoles can also be done from an X "
"Window instance with the <keycombo> <keycap>Ctrl</keycap> <keycap>Alt</"
"keycap> <keycap>Fx</keycap> </keycombo> key combination, but the mouse copy "
"operation does not work between the graphical interface and a virtual "
"console. You can return to the X Window display with the <keycombo> "
"<keycap>Ctrl</keycap> <keycap>Alt</keycap> <keycap>Fx</keycap> </keycombo> "
"combination, where <keycap>Fx</keycap> is usually <keycap>F1</keycap> but "
"may be <keycap>F7</keycap>."
msgstr ""
"참고로, 가상 콘솔 간의 전환은 <keycombo> <keycap>Ctrl</keycap> <keycap>Alt</"
"keycap> <keycap>Fx</keycap> </keycombo> 키 조합을 사용하여 X 윈도우 인스턴스"
"에서도 수행할 수 있지만, 그래픽 인터페이스와 가상 콘솔 사이에서는 마우스를 이"
"용한 복사 안 됩니다. <keycombo> <keycap>Ctrl</keycap> <keycap>Alt</keycap> "
"<keycap>Fx</keycap> </keycombo> 조합을 사용하여 X 윈도우 화면으로 돌아갈 수 "
"있으며, 여기서 <keycap>Fx</keycap>가 보통 <keycap>F1</keycap>이지만 "
"<keycap>F7</keycap>일 수도 있습니다."

#. type: Attribute 'xreflabel' of: <chapter>
#: en/chapter11/chapter11.xml:8
msgid "Chapter&nbsp;11"
msgstr "제11장"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><title>
#: en/chapter11/chapter11.xml:12 en/chapter11/theend.xml:11
msgid "The End"
msgstr "마치며"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><title>
#: en/chapter11/getcounted.xml:11
msgid "Get Counted"
msgstr "등록하기"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/chapter11/getcounted.xml:13
msgid ""
"Now that you have finished the book, do you want to be counted as an LFS "
"user? Head over to <ulink url=\"&lfs-root;cgi-bin/lfscounter.php\"/> and "
"register as an LFS user by entering your name and the first LFS version you "
"have used."
msgstr ""
"이제 책을 마쳤으니, LFS 사용자로서 등록하기를 원하시나요? <ulink url=\"&lfs-"
"root;cgi-bin/lfscounter.php\"/> 로 이동하여 여러분의 이름과 처음으로 사용한 "
"LFS 버전을 입력하고 LFS 사용자로 등록하십시오."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/chapter11/getcounted.xml:18
msgid "Let's reboot into LFS now."
msgstr "지금 LFS로 리부트."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><title>
#: en/chapter11/reboot.xml:11
msgid "Rebooting the System"
msgstr "시스템 리부팅"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/chapter11/reboot.xml:13
msgid ""
"Now that all of the software has been installed, it is time to reboot your "
"computer. However, there are still a few things to check.  Here are some "
"suggestions:"
msgstr ""
"이제 모든 소프트웨어가 설치되었으므로, 컴퓨터를 재부팅할 시간입니다. 그러나, "
"그전에 아직 몇 가지 확인해야 할 것이 있습니다. 몇 가지 제안 사항:"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/chapter11/reboot.xml:71
msgid ""
"Install any <ulink url='&blfs-book;postlfs/firmware.html'>firmware</ulink> "
"needed if the kernel driver for your hardware requires some firmware files "
"to function properly."
msgstr ""
"하드웨어용 커널 드라이버가 제대로 작동하기 위해 특정 펌웨어 파일이 필요하면, "
"필요한 <ulink url='&blfs-book;postlfs/firmware.html'>펌웨어</ulink>를 설치하"
"십시오."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/chapter11/reboot.xml:80
msgid "Ensure a password is set for the &root; user."
msgstr "&root; 사용자 비밀번호가 설정되어 있는지 확인하십시오."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/chapter11/reboot.xml:86
msgid ""
"A review of the following configuration files is also appropriate at this "
"point."
msgstr "이 시점에서 다음 설정 파일들을 검토하는 것도 좋습니다."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/chapter11/reboot.xml:95
msgid "/etc/resolv.conf <phrase revision='systemd'>(optional)</phrase>"
msgstr "/etc/resolv.conf <phrase revision='systemd'>(optional)</phrase>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/chapter11/reboot.xml:98
msgid "/etc/sysconfig/ifconfig.eth0"
msgstr "/etc/sysconfig/ifconfig.eth0"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/chapter11/reboot.xml:103
msgid ""
"Now that we have said that, let's move on to booting our shiny new LFS "
"installation for the first time! <emphasis>First exit from the chroot "
"environment</emphasis>:"
msgstr ""
"방금 주의 사항을 말씀드렸으니, 이제 우리가 만든 빛나는 새 LFS 시스템을 처음으"
"로 부팅해 봅시다! 먼저 <emphasis>chroot 환경에서 나갑니다</emphasis>:"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><screen>
#: en/chapter11/reboot.xml:107
#, no-wrap
msgid "<userinput>logout</userinput>"
msgstr "<userinput>logout</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/chapter11/reboot.xml:110
msgid "Then unmount the virtual file systems:"
msgstr "가상 파일 시스템 언마운트:"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><screen>
#: en/chapter11/reboot.xml:112
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<userinput>umount -v $LFS/dev/pts\n"
"mountpoint -q $LFS/dev/shm &amp;&amp; umount -v $LFS/dev/shm\n"
"umount -v $LFS/dev\n"
"umount -v $LFS/run\n"
"umount -v $LFS/proc\n"
"umount -v $LFS/sys</userinput>"
msgstr ""
"<userinput>umount -v $LFS/dev/pts\n"
"mountpoint -q $LFS/dev/shm &amp;&amp; umount -v $LFS/dev/shm\n"
"umount -v $LFS/dev\n"
"umount -v $LFS/run\n"
"umount -v $LFS/proc\n"
"umount -v $LFS/sys</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/chapter11/reboot.xml:119
msgid ""
"If multiple partitions were created, unmount the other partitions before "
"unmounting the main one, like this:"
msgstr ""
"여러 파티션을 생성했다면, 다음과 같이 다른 파티션들을 먼저 언마운트한 다음 "
"주 파티션을 언마운트하십시오. 이렇게:"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><screen>
#: en/chapter11/reboot.xml:122
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<userinput>umount -v $LFS/home\n"
"umount -v $LFS</userinput>"
msgstr ""
"<userinput>umount -v $LFS/home\n"
"umount -v $LFS</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/chapter11/reboot.xml:125
msgid "Unmount the LFS file system itself:"
msgstr "LFS 파일시스템 언마운트:"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><screen>
#: en/chapter11/reboot.xml:127
#, no-wrap
msgid "<userinput>umount -v $LFS</userinput>"
msgstr "<userinput>umount -v $LFS</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/chapter11/reboot.xml:129
msgid "Now, reboot the system."
msgstr "지금, 시스템 리부팅."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/chapter11/reboot.xml:136
msgid ""
"Assuming the GRUB boot loader was set up as outlined earlier, the menu is "
"set to boot <emphasis>LFS &version;</emphasis> automatically."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/chapter11/reboot.xml:139
msgid ""
"When the reboot is complete, the LFS system is ready for use.  What you will "
"see is a simple <quote>login: </quote> prompt.  At this point, you can "
"proceed to <ulink url=\"&blfs-book;\">the BLFS Book</ulink> where you can "
"add more software to suit your needs."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/chapter11/reboot.xml:145
msgid ""
"If your reboot is <emphasis role=\"bold\">not</emphasis> successful, it is "
"time to troubleshoot.  For hints on solving initial booting problems, see "
"<ulink url=\"https://www.linuxfromscratch.org/lfs/troubleshooting.html\"/>."
msgstr ""
"재부팅 성공이 <emphasis role=\"bold\">아니라면</emphasis>, 이제 문제를 해결"
"(troubleshoot)할 때입니다. 초기 부팅 문제를 해결하는 데 도움이 되는 힌트 "
"<ulink url=\"https://www.linuxfromscratch.org/lfs/troubleshooting.html\"/>."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><indexterm><primary>
#: en/chapter11/theend.xml:14
msgid "/etc/lfs-release"
msgstr "/etc/lfs-release"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><indexterm><primary>
#: en/chapter11/theend.xml:18
msgid "/etc/lsb-release"
msgstr "/etc/lsb-release"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><indexterm><primary>
#: en/chapter11/theend.xml:22
msgid "/etc/os-release"
msgstr "/etc/os-release"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/chapter11/theend.xml:25
msgid ""
"Well done! The new LFS system is installed! We wish you much success with "
"your shiny new custom-built Linux system."
msgstr ""
"참 잘 했어요! 새 LFS 시스템이 설치되었습니다! 여러분이 직접 빌드하여 빛나는 "
"이 새로운 맞춤형 리눅스 시스템과 함께 큰 성공을 거두시길 바랍니다."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/chapter11/theend.xml:28
msgid ""
"It may be a good idea to create an <filename>/etc/lfs-release</filename> "
"file. By having this file, it is very easy for you (and for us if you need "
"to ask for help at some point) to find out which LFS version is installed on "
"the system. Create this file by running:"
msgstr ""
"<filename>/etc/lfs-release</filename> 파일을 만드는 것이 좋습니다. 이 파일이 "
"있으면 시스템에 설치된 LFS 버전이 무엇인지 여러분이 확인하기에(그리고 나중에 "
"도움을 요청할 일이 생겼을 때 우리가 확인하기에도) 매우 편리합니다. 다음 명령"
"을 실행하여 이 파일을 생성:"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><screen>
#: en/chapter11/theend.xml:34
#, no-wrap
msgid "<userinput>echo &version; &gt; /etc/lfs-release</userinput>"
msgstr "<userinput>echo &version; &gt; /etc/lfs-release</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/chapter11/theend.xml:36
msgid ""
"Two files describing the installed system may be used by packages that can "
"be installed on the system later, either in binary form or by building them."
msgstr ""
"설치된 시스템을 설명하는 두 파일은 나중에 시스템에 설치될 패키지들이 바이너"
"리 형태이거나 혹은 직접 빌드하는 경우 모두에서 사용될 수 있습니다."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/chapter11/theend.xml:40
msgid ""
"The first one shows the status of your new system with respect to the Linux "
"Standards Base (LSB).  To create this file, run:"
msgstr ""
"첫 번째 파일은 리눅스 표준 베이스(LSB)와 관련된 새 시스템의 상태를 보여줍니"
"다. 이 파일을 만들려면 다음을 실행:"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><screen>
#: en/chapter11/theend.xml:44
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<userinput>cat &gt; /etc/lsb-release &lt;&lt; \"EOF\"\n"
"DISTRIB_ID=\"Linux From Scratch\"\n"
"DISTRIB_RELEASE=\"&version;\"\n"
"DISTRIB_CODENAME=\"&lt;your name here&gt;\"\n"
"DISTRIB_DESCRIPTION=\"Linux From Scratch\"\n"
"EOF</userinput>"
msgstr ""
"<userinput>cat &gt; /etc/lsb-release &lt;&lt; \"EOF\"\n"
"DISTRIB_ID=\"Linux From Scratch\"\n"
"DISTRIB_RELEASE=\"&version;\"\n"
"DISTRIB_CODENAME=\"&lt;your name here&gt;\"\n"
"DISTRIB_DESCRIPTION=\"Linux From Scratch\"\n"
"EOF</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/chapter11/theend.xml:51
msgid ""
"The second one contains roughly the same information, and is used by systemd "
"and some graphical desktop environments.  To create this file, run:"
msgstr ""
"두 번째 파일에는 거의 같은 정보가 들어가며, systemd 및 일부 그래픽 데스크톱 "
"환경에서 쓰입니다. 이 파일을 만들려면 실행:"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><screen>
#: en/chapter11/theend.xml:55
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<userinput>cat &gt; /etc/os-release &lt;&lt; \"EOF\"\n"
"NAME=\"Linux From Scratch\"\n"
"VERSION=\"&version;\"\n"
"ID=lfs\n"
"PRETTY_NAME=\"Linux From Scratch &version;\"\n"
"VERSION_CODENAME=\"&lt;your name here&gt;\"\n"
"HOME_URL=\"&lfs-root;lfs/\"\n"
"RELEASE_TYPE=\"&os-release-type;\"\n"
"EOF</userinput>"
msgstr ""
"<userinput>cat &gt; /etc/os-release &lt;&lt; \"EOF\"\n"
"NAME=\"Linux From Scratch\"\n"
"VERSION=\"&version;\"\n"
"ID=lfs\n"
"PRETTY_NAME=\"Linux From Scratch &version;\"\n"
"VERSION_CODENAME=\"&lt;your name here&gt;\"\n"
"HOME_URL=\"&lfs-root;lfs/\"\n"
"RELEASE_TYPE=\"&os-release-type;\"\n"
"EOF</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/chapter11/theend.xml:65
msgid ""
"Be sure to customize the fields 'DISTRIB_CODENAME' and 'VERSION_CODENAME' to "
"make the system uniquely yours."
msgstr ""
"'DISTRIB_CODENAME'과 'VERSION_CODENAME' 필드를 여러분만의 값으로 설정하여 여"
"러분의 시스템을 독자적인 것으로 만드십시오."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><title>
#: en/chapter11/whatnow.xml:11
msgid "Additional Resources"
msgstr "추가 리소스"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/chapter11/whatnow.xml:13
msgid ""
"Thank you for reading this LFS book. We hope that you have found this book "
"helpful and have learned more about the system creation process."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/chapter11/whatnow.xml:17
msgid ""
"Now that the LFS system is installed, you may be wondering <quote>What next?"
"</quote> To answer that question, we have compiled a list of resources for "
"you."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/chapter11/whatnow.xml:24
msgid "Maintenance"
msgstr "유지관리"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/chapter11/whatnow.xml:26
msgid ""
"Bugs and security notices are reported regularly for all software.  Since an "
"LFS system is compiled from source, it is up to you to keep abreast of such "
"reports.  There are several online resources that track such reports, some "
"of which are shown below:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/chapter11/whatnow.xml:34
msgid ""
"<ulink url=\"&lfs-root;lfs/advisories/\">LFS Security Advisories</ulink>"
msgstr "<ulink url=\"&lfs-root;lfs/advisories/\">LFS 보안 권고</ulink>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/chapter11/whatnow.xml:36
msgid ""
"This is a list of security vulnerabilities discovered in the LFS book after "
"it's published."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/chapter11/whatnow.xml:41
msgid ""
"<ulink url=\"https://seclists.org/oss-sec/\">Open Source Security Mailing "
"List</ulink>"
msgstr ""
"<ulink url=\"https://seclists.org/oss-sec/\">오픈 소스 보안 메일링 리스트</"
"ulink>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/chapter11/whatnow.xml:44
msgid ""
"This is a mailing list for discussion of security flaws, concepts, and "
"practices in the Open Source community."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/chapter11/whatnow.xml:61
msgid "LFS Hints"
msgstr "LFS 힌트"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/chapter11/whatnow.xml:63
msgid ""
"The LFS Hints are a collection of educational documents submitted by "
"volunteers in the LFS community. The hints are available at <ulink "
"url=\"&hints-root;\"/>."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/chapter11/whatnow.xml:69
msgid "Mailing lists"
msgstr "메일링 리스트"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/chapter11/whatnow.xml:71
msgid ""
"There are several LFS mailing lists you may subscribe to if you are in need "
"of help, want to stay current with the latest developments, want to "
"contribute to the project, and more. See <xref linkend=\"ch-intro-"
"maillists\"/> for more information."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/chapter11/whatnow.xml:81
msgid ""
"The goal of The Linux Documentation Project (TLDP) is to collaborate on all "
"of the issues of Linux documentation. The TLDP features a large collection "
"of HOWTOs, guides, and man pages.  It is located at <ulink url=\"https://"
"tldp.org/\"/>."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><part><title>
#: en/index.xml:22
msgid "Preparing for the Build"
msgstr "빌드 준비"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><title>
#: en/index.xml:30
msgid "Building the LFS Cross Toolchain and Temporary Tools"
msgstr "LFS 크로스 툴체인 및 임시 도구"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><title>
#: en/index.xml:39
msgid "Building the LFS System"
msgstr "LFS시스템 빌드"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><title>
#: en/index.xml:48
msgid "Appendices"
msgstr "부록"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><title>
#: en/part3intro/generalinstructions.xml:9
#: en/part3intro/generalinstructions.xml:12
msgid "General Compilation Instructions"
msgstr "일반 컴파일 지침"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><caution><para>
#: en/part3intro/generalinstructions.xml:16
msgid ""
"During a development cycle of LFS, the instructions in the book are often "
"modified to adapt for a package update or take the advantage of new features "
"from updated packages.  Mixing up the instructions of different versions of "
"the LFS book can cause subtle breakages.  This kind of issue is generally a "
"result from reusing some script created for a prior LFS release.  Such a "
"reuse is strongly discouraged.  If you are reusing scripts for a prior LFS "
"release for any reason, you'll need to be very careful to update the scripts "
"to match current version of the LFS book."
msgstr ""
"LFS 개발 주기 동안 책의 지침은 패키지 업데이트에 맞추거나 업데이트된 패키지"
"의 새로운 기능을 활용하기 위해 자주 수정됩니다. 서로 다른 버전의 LFS 책에 담"
"긴 지침을 섞어서 사용하면 미묘한 결함이 발생할 수 있습니다. 이런 종류의 문제"
"는 일반적으로 이전 LFS 릴리스를 위해 만들었던 스크립트를 재사용할 때 발생합니"
"다. 이러한 재사용은 강력히 권장하지 않습니다. 만약 어떤 이유로든 이전 LFS 릴"
"리스의 스크립트를 재사용한다면, 현재 버전의 LFS 책과 일치하도록 스크립트를 매"
"우 주의 깊게 업데이트해야 합니다."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/part3intro/generalinstructions.xml:28
msgid "Here are some things you should know about building each package:"
msgstr "각 패키지를 빌드할 때 알아두어야 할 몇 가지 사항:"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/part3intro/generalinstructions.xml:33
msgid ""
"Several packages are patched before compilation, but only when the patch is "
"needed to circumvent a problem. A patch is often needed in both the current "
"and the following chapters, but sometimes, when the same package is built "
"more than once, the patch is not needed right away.  Therefore, do not be "
"concerned if instructions for a downloaded patch seem to be missing.  "
"Warning messages about <emphasis>offset</emphasis> or <emphasis>fuzz</"
"emphasis> may also be encountered when applying a patch. Do not worry about "
"these warnings; the patch was still successfully applied."
msgstr ""
"여러 패키지는 컴파일 전에 패치가 적용되지만, 이는 오직 문제를 해결하기 위해 "
"패치가 필요한 경우에만 해당합니다. 현재 장과 다음 장 모두에서 패치가 필요한 "
"경우가 많지만, 때로는 똑같은 패키지가 여러 번 빌드될 때 당장은 패치가 필요치 "
"않을 수도 있습니다. 그러므로 다운로드한 패치에 대한 지침이 없는 것처럼 보이더"
"라도 걱정하지 마십시오. 패치를 적용할 때 <emphasis>offset</emphasis> 또는 "
"<emphasis>fuzz</emphasis>에 대한 경고 메시지가 나타날 수도 있습니다. 이러한 "
"경고에 대해서는 걱정하지 마십시오. 패치는 여전히 성공적으로 적용된 것입니다."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/part3intro/generalinstructions.xml:45
msgid ""
"During the compilation of most packages, some warnings will scroll by on the "
"screen. These are normal and can safely be ignored.  These warnings are "
"usually about deprecated, but not invalid, use of the C or C++ syntax. C "
"standards change fairly often, and some packages have not yet been updated. "
"This is not a serious problem, but it does cause the warnings to appear."
msgstr ""
"대부분의 패키지를 컴파일하는 동안 화면에 몇 가지 경고 메시지가 지나갈 것입니"
"다. 이는 정상적인 현상이며 안심하고 무시하셔도 됩니다. 이러한 경고는 보통 권"
"장되지 않지만(deprecated) 유효하지 않은 것은 아닌 C 또는 C++ 구문 사용에 관"
"한 것입니다. C 표준은 상당히 자주 바뀌며, 일부 패키지는 아직 업데이트되지 않"
"았을 뿐입니다. 이는 심각한 문제가 아니지만, 경고 메시지가 나타나는 원인이 됩"
"니다."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/part3intro/generalinstructions.xml:54
msgid ""
"Check one last time that the <envar>LFS</envar> environment variable is set "
"up properly:"
msgstr ""
"Check one last time that the <envar>LFS</envar> environment variable is set "
"up properly:"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/part3intro/generalinstructions.xml:59
msgid ""
"Make sure the output shows the path to the LFS partition's mount point, "
"which is <filename class=\"directory\">/mnt/lfs</filename>, using our "
"example."
msgstr ""
"우리 예제에 따라, 출력 결과에 LFS 파티션의 마운트 지점 <filename "
"class=\"directory\">/mnt/lfs</filename> 디렉터리 경로가 표시되는지 확인하십시"
"오."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/part3intro/generalinstructions.xml:66
msgid "Finally, two important items must be emphasized:"
msgstr "마지막으로, 두 가지 중요한 사항을 반드시 강조해야 합니다:"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><important><para>
#: en/part3intro/generalinstructions.xml:70
msgid ""
"The build instructions assume that the <xref linkend='ch-partitioning-"
"hostreqs'/>, including symbolic links, have been set properly:"
msgstr ""
"빌드 지침은 심볼릭 링크를 포함하여 <xref linkend='ch-partitioning-hostreqs'/"
"> 이 적절히 설정되었다고 가정:"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><important><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/part3intro/generalinstructions.xml:76
msgid "<command>bash</command> is the shell in use."
msgstr "<command>bash</command> is the shell in use."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><important><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/part3intro/generalinstructions.xml:79
msgid "<command>sh</command> is a symbolic link to <command>bash</command>."
msgstr "<command>sh</command> is a symbolic link to <command>bash</command>."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><important><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/part3intro/generalinstructions.xml:82
msgid ""
"<command>/usr/bin/awk</command> is a symbolic link to <command>gawk</"
"command>."
msgstr ""
"<command>/usr/bin/awk</command> is a symbolic link to <command>gawk</"
"command>."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><important><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/part3intro/generalinstructions.xml:85
msgid ""
"<command>/usr/bin/yacc</command> is a symbolic link to <command>bison</"
"command>, or to a small script that executes bison."
msgstr ""
"<command>/usr/bin/yacc</command> is a symbolic link to <command>bison</"
"command>, or to a small script that executes bison."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><important><para>
#: en/part3intro/generalinstructions.xml:93
msgid "Here is a synopsis of the build process."
msgstr "빌드 과정의 개요는 다음과 같습니다."

#.  Do
#.           <emphasis>
#. not</emphasis> put sources in
#.           <filename class="directory">/mnt/lfs/tools/</filename>. 
#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><important><orderedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/part3intro/generalinstructions.xml:97
msgid ""
"Place all the sources and patches in a directory that will be accessible "
"from the chroot environment, such as <filename class=\"directory\">/mnt/lfs/"
"sources/</filename>."
msgstr ""
"모든 소스 파일과 패치를 chroot 환경에서 접근 가능한 <filename "
"class=\"directory\">/mnt/lfs/sources/</filename> 같은 디렉터리에 배치하십시"
"오."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><important><orderedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/part3intro/generalinstructions.xml:104
msgid ""
"Change to the <filename class=\"directory\">/mnt/lfs/sources/</filename> "
"directory."
msgstr ""
"<filename class=\"directory\">/mnt/lfs/sources/</filename> 디렉터리로 이동."

#. type: Attribute 'xreflabel' of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><important><orderedlist><listitem>
#: en/part3intro/generalinstructions.xml:106
msgid "Package build instructions"
msgstr "패키지 빌드 명령"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><important><orderedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/part3intro/generalinstructions.xml:107
msgid "For each package:"
msgstr "각 패키지:"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><important><orderedlist><listitem><orderedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/part3intro/generalinstructions.xml:110
msgid ""
"Using the <command>tar</command> program, extract the package to be built.  "
"In <xref linkend=\"chapter-cross-tools\"/> and <xref linkend=\"chapter-"
"temporary-tools\"/>, ensure you are the <emphasis>lfs</emphasis> user when "
"extracting the package."
msgstr ""
"<command>tar</command> 프로그램을 사용하여 빌드할 패키지의 압축을 푸십시오. "
"<xref linkend=\"chapter-cross-tools\"/> 및 <xref linkend=\"chapter-temporary-"
"tools\"/> 에서는 패키지 압축을 풀 때 반드시 <emphasis>lfs</emphasis> 사용자 "
"권한인지 확인하십시오."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><important><orderedlist><listitem><orderedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/part3intro/generalinstructions.xml:114
msgid ""
"Do not use any method except the <command>tar</command> command to extract "
"the source code. Notably, using the <command>cp -R</command> command to copy "
"the source code tree somewhere else can destroy timestamps in the source "
"tree, and cause the build to fail."
msgstr ""
"소스 코드를 추출할 때는 <command>tar</command> 명령 이외의 어떠한 방법도 사용"
"하지 마십시오. 특히 <command>cp -R</command> 명령을 사용하여 소스 코드 트리"
"를 다른 곳으로 복사하는 것은 소스 트리의 타임스탬프를 손상시켜 빌드 실패를 초"
"래할 수 있습니다."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><important><orderedlist><listitem><orderedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/part3intro/generalinstructions.xml:121
msgid "Change to the directory created when the package was extracted."
msgstr "패키지의 압축을 풀 때 생성된 디렉터리로 이동하십시오."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><important><orderedlist><listitem><orderedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/part3intro/generalinstructions.xml:125
msgid "Follow the instructions for building the package."
msgstr "패키지 빌드를 위한 지침을 따르십시오."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><important><orderedlist><listitem><orderedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/part3intro/generalinstructions.xml:128
msgid "Change back to the sources directory when the build is complete."
msgstr "빌드가 완료되면 sources 디렉터리로 다시 이동하십시오."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><important><orderedlist><listitem><orderedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/part3intro/generalinstructions.xml:131
msgid "Delete the extracted source directory unless instructed otherwise."
msgstr "별도의 지시가 없는 한, 압축을 풀었던 소스 디렉터리를 삭제하십시오."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/part3intro/introduction.xml:13
msgid ""
"This part is divided into three stages: first, building a cross compiler and "
"its associated libraries; second, using this cross toolchain to build "
"several utilities in a way that isolates them from the host distribution; "
"and third, entering the chroot environment (which further improves host "
"isolation) and constructing the remaining tools needed to build the final "
"system."
msgstr ""
"이 부분은 세 단계로 나뉩니다. 첫째, 크로스 컴파일러와 관련 라이브러리를 빌드"
"합니다. 둘째, 이 크로스 툴체인을 사용하여 호스트 배포판으로부터 격리된 방식으"
"로 여러 유틸리티를 빌드합니다. 셋째, (호스트 격리를 더욱 강화하는) chroot 환"
"경으로 진입하여 최종 시스템을 빌드하는 데 필요한 나머지 도구들을 구축합니다."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><important><para>
#: en/part3intro/introduction.xml:20
msgid ""
"This is where the real work of building a new system begins. Be very careful "
"to follow the instructions exactly as the book shows them. You should try to "
"understand what each command does, and no matter how eager you are to finish "
"your build, you should refrain from blindly typing the commands as shown. "
"Read the documentation when there is something you do not understand. Also, "
"keep track of your typing and of the output of commands, by using the "
"<command>tee</command> utility to send the terminal output to a file. This "
"makes debugging easier if something goes wrong."
msgstr ""
"여기서부터 새 시스템을 빌드하는 실제 작업이 시작됩니다. 책에 나온 지시 사항"
"을 정확하게 따르도록 매우 주의하십시오. 각 명령어가 무엇을 하는지 이해하려고 "
"해야 하며, 빌드를 빨리 끝내고 싶더라도 명령어를 무작정 입력하는 것은 삼가야 "
"합니다. 이해 안 되는 부분이 있다면 문서를 읽어보십시오. 또한, <command>tee</"
"command> 유틸리티를 사용하여 터미널 출력을 파일로 보냄으로써 사용자가 입력한 "
"내용과 명령어의 출력 결과를 기록해 두십시오. 이렇게 하면 문제가 발생했을 때 "
"디버깅하기가 더 쉬워집니다."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/part3intro/introduction.xml:30
msgid ""
"The next section is a technical introduction to the build process, while the "
"following one presents <emphasis role=\"strong\">very important</emphasis> "
"general instructions."
msgstr ""
"다음 섹션은 빌드 과정에 대한 기술적인 소개이며, 그 뒤에 이어지는 섹션은 "
"<emphasis role=\"strong\">매우 중요한</emphasis> 일반 지침을 다룹니다."

#. type: Content of: <preface><title>
#: en/part3intro/part3intro.xml:12
msgid "Important Preliminary Material"
msgstr "중요한 사전 준비사항"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><title>
#: en/part3intro/toolchaintechnotes.xml:11
#: en/part3intro/toolchaintechnotes.xml:14
msgid "Toolchain Technical Notes"
msgstr "툴체인 기술 노트"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/part3intro/toolchaintechnotes.xml:16
msgid ""
"This section explains some of the rationale and technical details behind the "
"overall build method. Don't try to immediately understand everything in this "
"section. Most of this information will be clearer after performing an actual "
"build. Come back and re-read this chapter at any time during the build "
"process."
msgstr ""
"이 섹션은 전체적인 빌드 방식 뒤에 숨겨진 몇 가지 이론적 근거와 기술적 세부 사"
"항을 설명합니다. 이 섹션의 모든 내용을 즉시 이해하려고 애쓰지 마십시오. 대부"
"분의 정보는 실제 빌드를 수행한 후에 더 명확해질 것입니다. 빌드 과정 중 언제라"
"도 다시 돌아와 이 장을 읽어보십시오."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/part3intro/toolchaintechnotes.xml:22
msgid ""
"The overall goal of <xref linkend=\"chapter-cross-tools\"/> and <xref "
"linkend=\"chapter-temporary-tools\"/> is to produce a temporary area "
"containing a set of tools that are known to be good, and that are isolated "
"from the host system.  By using the <command>chroot</command> command, the "
"compilations in the remaining chapters will be isolated within that "
"environment, ensuring a clean, trouble-free build of the target LFS system. "
"The build process has been designed to minimize the risks for new readers, "
"and to provide the most educational value at the same time."
msgstr ""
"<xref linkend=\"chapter-cross-tools\"/> 및 <xref linkend=\"chapter-temporary-"
"tools\"/>의 전반적인 목표는 호스트 시스템으로부터 격리되고 상태가 검증된 도"
"구 모음을 포함하는 임시 영역을 생성하는 것입니다. <command>chroot</command> "
"명령을 사용하면 이후 장들의 컴파일 과정이 해당 환경 내에 격리되어, 대상 LFS "
"시스템의 깨끗하고 문제없는 빌드를 보장합니다. 빌드 과정은 새로운 독자들의 위"
"험을 최소화하는 동시에 교육적 가치를 극대화하도록 설계되었습니다."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/part3intro/toolchaintechnotes.xml:31
msgid ""
"This build process is based on <emphasis>cross-compilation</emphasis>. Cross-"
"compilation is normally used to build a compiler and its associated "
"toolchain for a machine different from the one that is used for the build. "
"This is not strictly necessary for LFS, since the machine where the new "
"system will run is the same as the one used for the build. But cross-"
"compilation has one great advantage: anything that is cross-compiled cannot "
"depend on the host environment."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><title>
#: en/part3intro/toolchaintechnotes.xml:39
#: en/part3intro/toolchaintechnotes.xml:41
msgid "About Cross-Compilation"
msgstr "크로스컴파일 관련"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><note><para>
#: en/part3intro/toolchaintechnotes.xml:45
msgid ""
"The LFS book is not (and does not contain) a general tutorial to build a "
"cross- (or native) toolchain. Don't use the commands in the book for a cross-"
"toolchain for some purpose other than building LFS, unless you really "
"understand what you are doing."
msgstr ""
"LFS 책은 크로스(또는 네이티브) 툴체인 빌드를 위한 일반적인 튜토리얼이 아니"
"며, 그러한 내용이 들어 있지도 않습니다. 여러분이 무엇을 하고 있는지 정말로 정"
"확히 이해하고 있는 게 아니라면, LFS를 빌드하는 것 이외의 다른 목적으로 이 책"
"의 크로스 툴체인용 명령어를 쓰지 마십시오."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><note><para>
#: en/part3intro/toolchaintechnotes.xml:52
msgid ""
"It's known installing GCC pass 2 will break the cross-toolchain.  We don't "
"consider it a bug because GCC pass 2 is the last package to be cross-"
"compiled in the book, and we won't <quote>fix</quote> it until we really "
"need to cross-compile some package after GCC pass 2 in the future."
msgstr ""
"GCC 패스 2 설치가 크로스 툴체인을 깨뜨린다는 것이 알려져 있습니다. 우리는 이"
"를 버그라고 생각하지 않는데, GCC 패스 2가 이 책에서 크로스 컴파일할 마지막 패"
"키지이기 때문입니다. 또한 향후 GCC 패스 2 이후에 다른 패키지를 크로스 컴파일"
"해야 할 진짜 필요가 생기기 전까지는 이를 <quote>수정</quote> 안 할 겁니다."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/part3intro/toolchaintechnotes.xml:60
msgid ""
"Cross-compilation involves some concepts that deserve a section of their "
"own. Although this section may be omitted on a first reading, coming back to "
"it later will help you gain a fuller understanding of the process."
msgstr ""
"Cross-compilation involves some concepts that deserve a section of their "
"own. Although this section may be omitted on a first reading, coming back to "
"it later will help you gain a fuller understanding of the process."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/part3intro/toolchaintechnotes.xml:65
msgid "Let us first define some terms used in this context."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/part3intro/toolchaintechnotes.xml:68
msgid "The build"
msgstr "The build"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/part3intro/toolchaintechnotes.xml:69
msgid ""
"is the machine where we build programs. Note that this machine is also "
"referred to as the <quote>host.</quote>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/part3intro/toolchaintechnotes.xml:73
msgid "The host"
msgstr "호스트"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/part3intro/toolchaintechnotes.xml:74
msgid ""
"is the machine/system where the built programs will run. Note that this use "
"of <quote>host</quote> is not the same as in other sections."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/part3intro/toolchaintechnotes.xml:79
msgid "The target"
msgstr "The target"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/part3intro/toolchaintechnotes.xml:80
msgid ""
"is only used for compilers. It is the machine the compiler produces code "
"for. It may be different from both the build and the host."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/part3intro/toolchaintechnotes.xml:87
msgid ""
"As an example, let us imagine the following scenario (sometimes referred to "
"as <quote>Canadian Cross</quote>). We have a compiler on a slow machine "
"only, let's call it machine A, and the compiler ccA. We also have a fast "
"machine (B), but no compiler for (B), and we want to produce code for a "
"third, slow machine (C). We will build a compiler for machine C in three "
"stages."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><informaltable><tgroup><thead><row><entry>
#: en/part3intro/toolchaintechnotes.xml:102
#: en/part3intro/toolchaintechnotes.xml:136
#: en/part3intro/toolchaintechnotes.xml:319
msgid "Stage"
msgstr "스테이지"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><informaltable><tgroup><thead><row><entry>
#: en/part3intro/toolchaintechnotes.xml:102
#: en/part3intro/toolchaintechnotes.xml:136
#: en/part3intro/toolchaintechnotes.xml:319
msgid "Build"
msgstr "Build"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><informaltable><tgroup><thead><row><entry>
#: en/part3intro/toolchaintechnotes.xml:102
#: en/part3intro/toolchaintechnotes.xml:136
#: en/part3intro/toolchaintechnotes.xml:319
msgid "Host"
msgstr "호스트"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><informaltable><tgroup><thead><row><entry>
#: en/part3intro/toolchaintechnotes.xml:103
#: en/part3intro/toolchaintechnotes.xml:137
#: en/part3intro/toolchaintechnotes.xml:320
msgid "Target"
msgstr "Target"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><informaltable><tgroup><thead><row><entry>
#: en/part3intro/toolchaintechnotes.xml:103
#: en/part3intro/toolchaintechnotes.xml:137
#: en/part3intro/toolchaintechnotes.xml:320
msgid "Action"
msgstr "Action"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><informaltable><tgroup><tbody><row><entry>
#: en/part3intro/toolchaintechnotes.xml:107
#: en/part3intro/toolchaintechnotes.xml:324
msgid "1"
msgstr "1"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><informaltable><tgroup><tbody><row><entry>
#: en/part3intro/toolchaintechnotes.xml:107
#: en/part3intro/toolchaintechnotes.xml:111
msgid "A"
msgstr "A"

